{"term":"1956","caseName":"Smith v. Sperling","caseLink":"https://www.oyez.org/cases/1956/316","caseTranscripts":[{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - March 28, 1957","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren6/oral_argument_audio/13300","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Number 316, Charles B. Smith, Petitioner, versus Milton Sperling et al.","start":0,"stop":9.903,"duration":9.9},{"text":"Mr. Williams, you may proceed.","start":9.903,"stop":15.587,"duration":5.68}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and members of the Supreme Court, at the recess yesterday afternoon, I had partially read to the Court the findings upon which we rely in this case and which I considered to be the very gist of the case.","start":15.587,"stop":39.13,"duration":23.54},{"text":"And therefore, I shall, with your permission, proceed to read the further findings which I believe to be pertinent.","start":39.13,"stop":48.811,"duration":9.68},{"text":"Finding 5 which appear on page 76 of the record is as follows.","start":48.811,"stop":56.29,"duration":7.48},{"text":"\"That it is not true either as alleged in the complaint or otherwise that all or a majority or any of the board of directors and officers of Warner Brothers Pictures, Inc., wrongfully participated in the acts in the complaint complained of, nor was said board of directors dominated or controlled by Harry M. Warner, Jack L. Warner, Albert Warner, Milton Sperling or anyone or more of them.","start":56.29,"stop":87.98,"duration":31.69},{"text":"It is not true that if demand had been made upon the Warner Brothers Pictures, Inc., that those to whom such application would be made to institute such suit would have been disqualified from faithfully doing their duty as directors and officers of said corporation, because of any matters or facts set forth in said complaint, or otherwise, that no demand was made on the directors of said Warner Brothers Pictures, Inc., to institute this action and that such demand would have been futile, nor was any demand addressed to the stockholders of said corporation that the stockholders of the said corporation were not at the time of the execution of the contract complained of, or at any time, or at all, under the domination or control of the three brothers, Warner.","start":87.98,"stop":142.626,"duration":54.65},{"text":"Nor was said corporation at any time herein referred to in hands or under control, antagonistic to the financial interests of said corporation and its stockholders.\"","start":142.626,"stop":158.109,"duration":15.48},{"text":"And the court --","start":158.109,"stop":158.335,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Of course, those findings are significant only if domination is a requirement.","start":158.335,"stop":166.775,"duration":8.44}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":166.775,"stop":166.852,"duration":0.08}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Because the Court -- if domination is not a requirement, the Court expressly found that a demand would have been futile --","start":166.852,"stop":174.674,"duration":7.82}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":174.674,"stop":175.171,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"-- and therefore, the absence of a demand would not officiate the jurisdiction?","start":175.171,"stop":180.887,"duration":5.72}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, Your Honor.","start":180.887,"stop":181.434,"duration":0.55}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"So that really, the findings beg the question as far as the problem we got here is concerned.","start":181.434,"stop":187.839,"duration":6.41}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I don't know that they begged the question because the problem we have here may turn on the question of domination.","start":187.839,"stop":193.871,"duration":6.03}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if -- of course, if domination is a prerequisite than the findings, I would suppose you can't get over those.","start":193.871,"stop":201.747,"duration":7.88}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, yes.","start":201.747,"stop":202.748,"duration":1},{"text":"Well, of course as I can --","start":202.748,"stop":203.778,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Domination is not a requirement.","start":203.778,"stop":206.976,"duration":3.2},{"text":"This finding is beside the point for this particular purpose.","start":206.976,"stop":210.199,"duration":3.22}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, Your Honor.","start":210.199,"stop":210.735,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":210.735,"stop":211.454,"duration":0.72}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, in connection with this matter of the demand would have been futile.","start":211.454,"stop":215.848,"duration":4.39},{"text":"Counsel has not given Your Honors the complete picture on that.","start":215.848,"stop":224.411,"duration":8.56},{"text":"The record shows, and I believe that -- it's at record page 588, the so-called admissions in connection with the futility of the findings and I think that the examination of the record is important because the record is what we're interested in.","start":224.411,"stop":250.174,"duration":25.76},{"text":"It appears at pages 587 and 586 in which the Court inquired of May, I should assume unless there is some contention expressly made to the contrary that this corporation would never have brought this suit.","start":250.174,"stop":271.433,"duration":21.26},{"text":"Is there any contention to the contrary?","start":271.433,"stop":276.689,"duration":5.26},{"text":"And I say, we don't make such a contention.","start":276.689,"stop":279.912,"duration":3.22},{"text":"Then, the Court -- I skip --","start":279.912,"stop":281.851,"duration":1.94},{"text":"And the Court goes down to say, “So far as demand and refusal are concerned, I take it that the defendant in effect stipulates in such a -- that a demand would have been futile.\"","start":281.851,"stop":292.216,"duration":10.37},{"text":"Mr. Williams, \"but not for the reasons alleged in the complaint.\"","start":292.216,"stop":295.497,"duration":3.28},{"text":"The Court, \"No, but for the reasons contended by the defendant.”","start":295.497,"stop":298.999,"duration":3.5},{"text":"Mr. Williams, “Certainly, not for the reason that the defendants ever contended that the contract was fraudulent.”","start":298.999,"stop":306.911,"duration":7.91},{"text":"The Court, \"As I understand, defendant's position and I can be corrected if I am in error, the defendant's position is that this was an advantageous arrangement for Warner -- for the Warner Corporation.","start":306.911,"stop":323.176,"duration":16.26},{"text":"And the directors would have -- have upheld it at any time against any attack by any person including any group of stockholders.\"","start":323.176,"stop":332.565,"duration":9.39},{"text":"Mr. Levy, “That is the position of both the individual defendants, Warner Brothers and the Corporation.","start":332.565,"stop":338.133,"duration":5.57},{"text":"All of them contend likewise.”","start":338.133,"stop":339.774,"duration":1.64},{"text":"Mr. Williams, “The individual defendants, Warner Brothers, are not involved in that issue.","start":339.774,"stop":345.426,"duration":5.65},{"text":"It is the corporation that is involved in that issue.”","start":345.426,"stop":349.372,"duration":3.95},{"text":"The Court, “And for those reasons, no matter what demand the plaintiff stockholder had made on the directors, they would never have brought this suit, is that a fair statement of it?”","start":349.372,"stop":359.229,"duration":9.86},{"text":"Mr. Williams, “Yes, that is a fair statement but not for the reasons alleged in the complaint that there was domination but for the reason and in the opinion of the responsible officers and directors of the corporation, this was a good contract.”","start":359.229,"stop":375.449,"duration":16.22},{"text":"The Court, “By good, you mean advantageous to the corporation?”","start":375.449,"stop":379.567,"duration":4.12},{"text":"Mr. Williams, “Advantageous to the Warner Corporation, yes.”","start":379.567,"stop":384.365,"duration":4.8},{"text":"Now, that is the so-called admission which was made and we regard it as a statement, rather than an admission, a statement of our position.","start":384.365,"stop":396.759,"duration":12.39},{"text":"Now, the findings which I have taken the liberty of reading to this Court were considered and the evidence supporting those findings was considered by the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit and the Court of Appeals found no reason to disturb the findings after the examination of the record.","start":396.759,"stop":420.575,"duration":23.82},{"text":"And so, stated at -- at page 5 of the Supplement Appendix 1 attached to the petition in this case where the opinion of the Court of Appeals is set forth in full.","start":420.575,"stop":434.886,"duration":14.31},{"text":"I, therefore, take it that in this case, we are justified in taking the position that the questions which will be decided by this Court, the basic questions of law, will be decided on the assumption that the findings of this Court determined of -- of the lower court, determined the facts, the Court will not in view of the record in this case and the type and character of the petition for the writ of certiorari and the -- that was filed will not go back of the Court's findings, the Court of Appeals having found that the findings were supported by the evidence.","start":434.886,"stop":481.531,"duration":46.64},{"text":"If I may narrow that, why I am -- I'm very seriously narrow because there has not been brought before this Court by any means, the -- the full evidence in the case, only a fragmentary portion of the evidence.","start":481.531,"stop":498.587,"duration":17.06},{"text":"Because we have assumed that in view of the opinion of the Court of Appeals that there would be no desire on the part of this Court to dig into the specific facts underlying the findings and -- and I am proceeding in my argument upon that theory.","start":498.587,"stop":518.053,"duration":19.47},{"text":"Now, counsel has said that he does not question the sufficiency of the evidence to support the findings.","start":518.053,"stop":531.431,"duration":13.38},{"text":"And on the other hand, he -- he -- at another point, he said in response to a question by one of the associate justices that he didn't think the evidence did support the findings and then at another point, he -- he went back to his original suggestion.","start":531.431,"stop":553.29,"duration":21.86},{"text":"What he has attempted to do, I believe, is without making an -- a direct attack upon the sufficiency of the evidence to support the findings, he has taken certain fragmentary and disconnected evidentiary facts and talked about them without giving the full story in any particular.","start":553.29,"stop":575.537,"duration":22.25},{"text":"And obviously, I cannot and do not believe I should.","start":575.537,"stop":578.522,"duration":2.99},{"text":"At this time, endeavor can beyond the Court's findings and try to engage in discussion as to what the evidence has been omitted in his statement or what other evidence was there.","start":578.522,"stop":591.209,"duration":12.69},{"text":"Now, we believe that the rule of law which has been established by this Court is as follows, we believe that this Court has stated that in a stockholder's derivative suit, the corporation will ordinarily and normally be aligned as a party plaintiff because it is the entity for whose benefit the action is being brought and the pursuit or entity which will recover the judgment if any.","start":591.209,"stop":635.018,"duration":43.81},{"text":"It is the real party in address.","start":635.018,"stop":638.454,"duration":3.44},{"text":"But, that there is an exception to that rule and that exception is a limited and special exception.","start":638.454,"stop":644.772,"duration":6.32},{"text":"When the corporation is a captive corporation, when it is in hands antagonistic to its financial analysts, when it is unable by reason of that captivity and being in such antagonistic hands to properly represent itself, there is an exception and in that case, it will be aligned as a party defendant.","start":644.772,"stop":672.483,"duration":27.71},{"text":"We believe that is the true meaning of Doctor versus Harrington.","start":672.483,"stop":676.659,"duration":4.18},{"text":"We believe that is the true meaning of Venner against the Great Northern and we respectfully submit to the Court that it is very tertiary and very well stated by this Court in the case of Koster against Lumbermens Mutual in which the Court epitomized the rule, as I understand it as follows.","start":676.659,"stop":700.712,"duration":24.05},{"text":"The cause of action which such a plaintiff, it is a stockholder, brings before the Court is not his own but the corporations.","start":700.712,"stop":710.878,"duration":10.17},{"text":"If it's the real party in interest and he is allowed to act in protection of its interests, somewhat as a next friend might do for an individual, because it is disabled from protecting itself, if however, such a case as this were treated in -- as other actions, the federal court would realign the parties for jurisdictional purposes according to their real interest.","start":710.878,"stop":740.844,"duration":29.97},{"text":"In this case, which his typical of many, this would put Lumbermens on the plaintiff's side.","start":740.844,"stop":748.608,"duration":7.76},{"text":"Illinois Corporations would then appear among plaintiffs and among defendants and jurisdiction would be ousted.","start":748.608,"stop":756.275,"duration":7.67}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"What would be the consequence of that rule in a situation where the stockholder is suing, not the directors but a third party?","start":756.275,"stop":768.403,"duration":12.13},{"text":"And where in that situation you would have no antagonism, no personal interest between the -- antagonistic interest between the interest of the directors and the corporation?","start":768.403,"stop":779.702,"duration":11.3}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"The corporation would automatically be -- be aligned as a plaintiff.","start":779.702,"stop":786.145,"duration":6.44},{"text":"I am now coming to the very --","start":786.145,"stop":786.543,"duration":0.4}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"But then if we let (Voice Overlap) as aligned as a plaintiff?","start":786.543,"stop":789.734,"duration":3.19}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"As a plaintiff.","start":789.734,"stop":790.849,"duration":1.12},{"text":"I am now coming to the very gist of the point when I read the last sentence of the quotation I was about -- that I was making.","start":790.849,"stop":799.339,"duration":8.49},{"text":"\"But jurisdiction is saved in this class of cases by a special dispensation because the corporation is in antagonistic hands.\"","start":799.339,"stop":812.847,"duration":13.51},{"text":"In other words, I believe the rule established by these cases, by this Court, is that the corporation will always be aligned as a plaintiff unless it is in antagonistic hands --","start":812.847,"stop":826.925,"duration":14.08}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What --","start":826.925,"stop":827.115,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"-- or is a captive corporation.","start":827.115,"stop":828.702,"duration":1.59}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What would have to be proven on -- according to your viewpoint in order to make it antagonistic?","start":828.702,"stop":835.063,"duration":6.36}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Would have to be proved?","start":835.063,"stop":835.92,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"In this case.","start":835.92,"stop":836.895,"duration":0.98}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"In this case, it would have to be proved that the directors or the majority of the directors were antagonistic to the interest of the corporation.","start":836.895,"stop":847.094,"duration":10.2},{"text":"That is between the corporation and the alleged wrong doers.","start":847.094,"stop":850.935,"duration":3.84},{"text":"They were willing to serve the interest of the wrong doers rather than the interest of the corporation.","start":850.935,"stop":856.324,"duration":5.39}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"In other words, they'd have to prove facts of what they allege as the ground for relief, would they?","start":856.324,"stop":861.442,"duration":5.12}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"In -- in our case --","start":861.442,"stop":864.085,"duration":2.64}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"They would have --","start":864.085,"stop":864.158,"duration":0.07}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"-- in this particular case --","start":864.158,"stop":865.632,"duration":1.47}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"They would have to prove that what the allege here is a basis for the recovery, setting aside to this contract, that these directors illegally, wrongfully in that state to pay -- conspired to do that.","start":865.632,"stop":879.13,"duration":13.5}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, Your Honor.","start":879.13,"stop":879.995,"duration":0.87}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"So that you -- from your standpoint, they have no jurisdiction unless they can recover on the merits.","start":879.995,"stop":887.856,"duration":7.86}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"In this particular case, yes.","start":887.856,"stop":889.106,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"In this particular case?","start":889.106,"stop":890.042,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"In this particular case.","start":890.042,"stop":891.237,"duration":1.19},{"text":"Well, I think --","start":891.237,"stop":891.509,"duration":0.27}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I -- has that -- has that been tried out?","start":891.509,"stop":895.315,"duration":3.81},{"text":"Have they -- has it issued and tried out here?","start":895.315,"stop":899.549,"duration":4.23}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":899.549,"stop":900.742,"duration":1.19}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the Court find that they did not illegally or wrongfully and in bad faith conspired?","start":900.742,"stop":906.022,"duration":5.28}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":906.022,"stop":906.731,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what it decided?","start":906.731,"stop":907.236,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I just got through reading the finding.","start":907.236,"stop":908.198,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Your argument -- your -- your argument here that -- that they have tested out the real basic issue in this basis?","start":908.198,"stop":913.943,"duration":5.75}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":913.943,"stop":914.775,"duration":0.83},{"text":"I say --","start":914.775,"stop":915.23,"duration":0.46}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"It shows the Court didn't have jurisdiction.","start":915.23,"stop":917.258,"duration":2.03}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":917.258,"stop":918.017,"duration":0.76},{"text":"I say in this particular case, Your Honor, the issue upon which the plaintiff sets his cause of action, puts his cause of action is coextensive with the issue, which the Court tries on the question of jurisdiction.","start":918.017,"stop":933.556,"duration":15.54}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That did -- they have decided here, put in our claim that they'd put in all the evidence that they had to show --","start":933.556,"stop":940.104,"duration":6.55}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":940.104,"stop":940.33,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- that they acted illegally and so forth.","start":940.33,"stop":942.367,"duration":2.04},{"text":"And then, can we really consider that as a moral --","start":942.367,"stop":945.322,"duration":2.96}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":945.322,"stop":946.233,"duration":0.91},{"text":"I will say this.","start":946.233,"stop":946.353,"duration":0.12}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- trial on the merits of the controversy?","start":946.353,"stop":949.29,"duration":2.94}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I will say this, if Your Honors please, that at page 588 of the record or 587 of the record, Mr. Levy, who represented the plaintiff in the case said that he -- \"I have no further evidence to offer.\"","start":949.29,"stop":974.021,"duration":24.73},{"text":"Now we had -- and that was on the issue of domination, which involved the very gist of the whole case.","start":974.021,"stop":982.075,"duration":8.05}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Was it on the issue of whether they had acted illegally and fraudulently and so forth?","start":982.075,"stop":986.662,"duration":4.59}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Naturally, because the issue of domination inevitably involved the whole question or the entire conduct with reference to this transaction.","start":986.662,"stop":997.016,"duration":10.35}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I thought, maybe I was wrong.","start":997.016,"stop":998.245,"duration":1.23},{"text":"Did I understand Mr. Levy to say that this issue have not been cited out and he had not been given a chance to try it out.","start":998.245,"stop":1005.201,"duration":6.96}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"What Mr. Levy said, if I understood him, and what I will say to is this.","start":1005.201,"stop":1010.605,"duration":5.4},{"text":"That the Court limited the taking of evidence to the question, the two questions of jurisdiction and statute of limitations which involve the same basic evidentiary matter.","start":1010.605,"stop":1024.098,"duration":13.49},{"text":"In this particular case, because of the allegations of the complaint, that evidence also necessarily included the very facts upon which the claim was based.","start":1024.098,"stop":1036.788,"duration":12.69},{"text":"And while we have not ever gotten to the merits of the case, we had put on all of the evidence, practically, all evidence on either side could have had on the merits because they were --","start":1036.788,"stop":1048.43,"duration":11.64}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"You really did try the merits though didn't you under your contention?","start":1048.43,"stop":1051.307,"duration":2.88}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":1051.307,"stop":1051.746,"duration":0.44},{"text":"No, we --","start":1051.746,"stop":1051.95,"duration":0.2}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Although you called it the jurisdiction, you --","start":1051.95,"stop":1053.989,"duration":2.04}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, we really --","start":1053.989,"stop":1054.528,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- reacted at the issue.","start":1054.528,"stop":1055.441,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, we really tried that issue.","start":1055.441,"stop":1057.403,"duration":1.96}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"The merit?","start":1057.403,"stop":1058.067,"duration":0.66}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1058.067,"stop":1058.297,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Are you suggesting that in this kind of a case, if a -- if a stockholder brings suit and on behalf of the corporation against a third person on the -- because the directors will not bring suit because they might have thought -- on a claim that he alleges the corporation pass.","start":1058.297,"stop":1087.237,"duration":28.94},{"text":"And he further alleges that he won't bring suit, that directors won't bring suit because the debtor, the potential debtor is a great friend of the majority of the directors and they don't want to bring suit against him which might put him in a bad public life.","start":1087.237,"stop":1104.693,"duration":17.46},{"text":"Is it your suggestion that on the question of jurisdiction being raised i.e. they're preventing the corporation from suing, the corporation would have to be a necessary party on one side or the other in such a suit, wouldn't it?","start":1104.693,"stop":1121.679,"duration":16.99}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Certainly.","start":1121.679,"stop":1122.633,"duration":0.95}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And on the question, whether it should be on the plaintiff's side or the defendant's side, is it your suggestion that the merits of the claim that is pressed must also be decided before you can decide the jurisdictional question as to what the real conflict is between the parties?","start":1122.633,"stop":1139.541,"duration":16.91}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":1139.541,"stop":1140.278,"duration":0.74},{"text":"I do not say that.","start":1140.278,"stop":1141.306,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Of course.","start":1141.306,"stop":1141.469,"duration":0.16}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I say that in this particular case.","start":1141.469,"stop":1143.76,"duration":2.29}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But I'm not saying about this case.","start":1143.76,"stop":1144.802,"duration":1.04}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes -- no, I don't say that.","start":1144.802,"stop":1145.428,"duration":0.63}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) --","start":1145.428,"stop":1146.755,"duration":1.33}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I say that the question of whether the real merits will be tried by the Court in this preliminary investigation and to its own jurisdiction must depend on the facts of each case as to whether the merits are or are not in disagreeably mixed-up with the -- with other questions.","start":1146.755,"stop":1168.334,"duration":21.58}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I suggest that the word \"antagonistic\" isn't that illuminating description.","start":1168.334,"stop":1173.6,"duration":5.27},{"text":"The word \"disabled\" used in the cost-cutting case is.","start":1173.6,"stop":1175.472,"duration":1.87}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I think -- yes.","start":1175.472,"stop":1177.049,"duration":1.58}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That means something.","start":1177.049,"stop":1177.944,"duration":0.89}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I think Your Honor is correct.","start":1177.944,"stop":1178.798,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Antagonistic gets you into other --","start":1178.798,"stop":1180.014,"duration":1.22}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"[Laughs]","start":1180.014,"stop":1180.809,"duration":0.8}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- to a totally different area.","start":1180.809,"stop":1182.073,"duration":1.26}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I think Your Honor is correct and -- and I think the word \"disabled\" is right and I -- and I was struck as -- with the appropriateness of the expression “captive corporation” which was used by some of the justices.","start":1182.073,"stop":1194.721,"duration":12.65}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Because if it isn't disabled, then the corporation must be the plaintiff?","start":1194.721,"stop":1198.685,"duration":3.96}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1198.685,"stop":1199.739,"duration":1.05},{"text":"Now, if Your Honor please, that puts in --","start":1199.739,"stop":1201.185,"duration":1.45}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Williams, before you get to --","start":1201.185,"stop":1202.965,"duration":1.78}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1202.965,"stop":1203.098,"duration":0.13}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Before you -- we get off of this subject, I -- I noticed in that sentence you read of Mr. Levy's on page 587, I have no further evidence to offer.","start":1203.098,"stop":1215.226,"duration":12.13},{"text":"The record shows also that he said, \"Under those circumstances.\"","start":1215.226,"stop":1218.87,"duration":3.64}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"That's -- that's when I had stated that --","start":1218.87,"stop":1220.88,"duration":2.01}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Now -- now preceding -- preceding that, is what he calls your admission and what you call your statement of your position.","start":1220.88,"stop":1229.351,"duration":8.47}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":1229.351,"stop":1229.929,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"But preceding that was a dialogue between the Court and Mr. Levy in which the Court said, \"Is there any further evidence to be offered on the issues as to jurisdiction limitation or latches?\"","start":1229.929,"stop":1245.344,"duration":15.41},{"text":"And Mr. Levy said, \"May it please the Court, I have been thinking over very carefully, some of the questions, Your Honor, propounded to me yesterday in our discussion with respect to the meaning of hostility, antagonism and so forth.","start":1245.344,"stop":1258.886,"duration":13.54},{"text":"I was wondering whether a cross-examination of the principal characters in this drama would shed any light on that particular subject.","start":1258.886,"stop":1267.259,"duration":8.37},{"text":"In the present state of the record Your Honor has before you the depositions of certain people.\"","start":1267.259,"stop":1274.245,"duration":6.99},{"text":"And then he goes on to say, \"I have not cross-examined any of these people.","start":1274.245,"stop":1278.934,"duration":4.69},{"text":"It may be that a cross-examination of them will yield further light on the question.","start":1278.934,"stop":1283.833,"duration":4.9},{"text":"Namely, is there hostility?","start":1283.833,"stop":1285.743,"duration":1.91},{"text":"Is there antagonism between the corporation as composed of the individuals who influenced its day-to-day conduct and responsible for its basic policy and so -- and so forth?\"","start":1285.743,"stop":1298.184,"duration":12.44},{"text":"And then comes what he calls your admission.","start":1298.184,"stop":1302.202,"duration":4.02},{"text":"And then he says, \"I have no further evidence to offer under those circumstances, but that would” -- would that not indicate that there was not a full hearing on the question of the interest of these people but that when he said, \"I have no further evidence to offer\" that it was in relation to a particular situation?","start":1302.202,"stop":1326.345,"duration":24.14}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":1326.345,"stop":1326.899,"duration":0.55},{"text":"If Your Honor please, it cannot possibly indicate that.","start":1326.899,"stop":1330.746,"duration":3.85},{"text":"In this case, the testimony of every director and of the number of officers who were not directors of Warner Brothers and other individuals was presented to the District Court.","start":1330.746,"stop":1345.562,"duration":14.82},{"text":"It was presented either by examination in open court or by the reading of their depositions.","start":1345.562,"stop":1351.802,"duration":6.24},{"text":"In the case of the depositions, the -- the officers and directors had been cross-examined at length by the counsel who appeared at the taping of the depositions.","start":1351.802,"stop":1365.031,"duration":13.23},{"text":"Consequently, the evidence was before the Court and in extensile before the Court.","start":1365.031,"stop":1372.615,"duration":7.58},{"text":"Two of the directors had testified for days.","start":1372.615,"stop":1378.586,"duration":5.97},{"text":"The depositions of all the other directors had been offered in evidence.","start":1378.586,"stop":1384.234,"duration":5.65},{"text":"A hundred in our exhibits have been received in evidence.","start":1384.234,"stop":1389.417,"duration":5.18},{"text":"The -- the testimony of numerable individuals had been received in evidence.","start":1389.417,"stop":1394.085,"duration":4.67},{"text":"The testimony of the plaintiffs by way of deposition had been received in evidence.","start":1394.085,"stop":1397.39,"duration":3.31}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Why -- why was the evidence as to -- of some directors by way of deposition --","start":1397.39,"stop":1402.543,"duration":5.15}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Because they were residence of New York and -- and Pennsylvania and depositions were taken for that reason.","start":1402.543,"stop":1413.427,"duration":10.88},{"text":"And we're taking some time in advance to the trial.","start":1413.427,"stop":1416.239,"duration":2.81}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"And its appropriate order, I suppose that's an order --","start":1416.239,"stop":1418.84,"duration":2.6}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"They were done by stipulation, I think.","start":1418.84,"stop":1420.235,"duration":1.39}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"By stipulation.","start":1420.235,"stop":1421.627,"duration":1.39}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"And now, Mr. Levy was thinking out loud and decided that he didn't want to ask anymore questions.","start":1421.627,"stop":1430.568,"duration":8.94},{"text":"He -- if he did want to ask any, all he had to do was say so.","start":1430.568,"stop":1435.481,"duration":4.91},{"text":"But he decided at that point as he said that under those circumstances I have no further evidence to offer.","start":1435.481,"stop":1443.51,"duration":8.03},{"text":"There was other evidence that I might have offered but I -- I felt that at that time, the entire factual picture wasn't before the Court.","start":1443.51,"stop":1453.848,"duration":10.34},{"text":"And so, I say that -- if Your Honors please, that there was as full and complete, a hearing of the facts upon which these findings are placed as -- as they could have well have been.","start":1453.848,"stop":1471.3,"duration":17.45},{"text":"And --","start":1471.3,"stop":1471.408,"duration":0.11}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"May I -- may I ask you a question?","start":1471.408,"stop":1472.526,"duration":1.12}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1472.526,"stop":1473.639,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I'd like to have your viewpoint.","start":1473.639,"stop":1474.931,"duration":1.29}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1474.931,"stop":1476.48,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"We can discuss it when it gets --","start":1476.48,"stop":1477.928,"duration":1.45}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1477.928,"stop":1478.23,"duration":0.3}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- into full rise.","start":1478.23,"stop":1478.825,"duration":0.6},{"text":"I'd like to have your viewpoint of it.","start":1478.825,"stop":1480.38,"duration":1.56},{"text":"I like to have your answer.","start":1480.38,"stop":1482.91,"duration":2.53},{"text":"What sort of proof of the allegation that it's made as to the invalidity of this contract and showing that the contract has been made by these -- to this company with these three men on the board of directors, a son-in-law, one of the Warner, under the circumstances they alleged.","start":1482.91,"stop":1504.659,"duration":21.75},{"text":"What sort of proof of those facts would you say would have been sufficient to hold that the -- that the Warner Brothers should be aligned as a defendant rather than a plaintiff?","start":1504.659,"stop":1518.084,"duration":13.42}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean the Warner Corporations?","start":1518.084,"stop":1519.818,"duration":1.73}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":1519.818,"stop":1520.15,"duration":0.33}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1520.15,"stop":1520.98,"duration":0.83}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I'd like to get your judgment to that.","start":1520.98,"stop":1523.7,"duration":2.72}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I think -- I think, if Your Honor please, in this particular case in view of the allegations of the complaint in this case that there is very little shot of that that -- that could have satisfied that point.","start":1523.7,"stop":1539.317,"duration":15.62},{"text":"In other words, this case is based upon the allegation that the brothers, Warner, two of the brothers Warner, conceived the idea of enriching the son-in-law of one of them at the expense of the corporation.","start":1539.317,"stop":1556.29,"duration":16.97},{"text":"And that they imposed this contract upon the corporation by virtue of the fact that they dominated and controlled the board of directors.","start":1556.29,"stop":1570.013,"duration":13.72},{"text":"That is the essence of the charge.","start":1570.013,"stop":1573.007,"duration":2.99},{"text":"Now, the essence of the charge then becomes the question -- the essence of the issue is was the board of directors dominated?","start":1573.007,"stop":1581.658,"duration":8.65},{"text":"In this particular case, the board of directors which approved the contract was the same board of directors which was on the -- was in -- man of the corporation with one exception.","start":1581.658,"stop":1592.802,"duration":11.14},{"text":"At this time, the suit was filed and that all of the intervening time.","start":1592.802,"stop":1597.541,"duration":4.74}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"How many directors were?","start":1597.541,"stop":1598.683,"duration":1.14}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Eleven.","start":1598.683,"stop":1599.997,"duration":1.31},{"text":"I might say that the record shows that Mr. Harry Warner and Jack Warner did not participate in the board meeting which approved this contract.","start":1599.997,"stop":1608.459,"duration":8.46}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What was their holding --","start":1608.459,"stop":1610.297,"duration":1.84}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"They held --","start":1610.297,"stop":1610.752,"duration":0.45}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- their holding to the total stock?","start":1610.752,"stop":1612.711,"duration":1.96}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"They held with their brother, Albert, a total of 15% of the stock.And the Court found that they did not have control of the corporation or the directors.","start":1612.711,"stop":1625.511,"duration":12.8},{"text":"Now, that brings us to a consideration of what I consider and I -- I may be wrong about it but I consider a very important element in this case.","start":1625.511,"stop":1638.593,"duration":13.08},{"text":"And of course, under the rule of Erie against Tompkins, this being a diversity case upon the merits.","start":1638.593,"stop":1647.787,"duration":9.19},{"text":"The -- the federal court will apply the law of the firm, the law of the State.","start":1647.787,"stop":1655.82,"duration":8.03},{"text":"And we have cited cases in our brief.","start":1655.82,"stop":1658.002,"duration":2.18},{"text":"On a point, there is one rather recent case in California that is particularly significant that involved the Douglas Aircraft Corporation, the case of Finley versus Garrett, in which the California rule in reference to this matter was laid down.","start":1658.002,"stop":1673.475,"duration":15.47},{"text":"There was a case where there was a -- a rather a very extensive claim alleged by a stockholder to subsist in favor of the corporation based upon part in the overreaching of the corporation, interlocking the right place and things of that sort and the man was made on the directors of -- of the Douglas Aircraft Corporation that they sue.","start":1673.475,"stop":1698.489,"duration":25.01},{"text":"And the matter rose on demurrer to the complaint, and the Court held.","start":1698.489,"stop":1705.759,"duration":7.27},{"text":"Now, here's the case where the directors in charge of the corporation at that time, the majority of the directors in charge of the corporation at the time that suit was demanded and refused are not shown by the allegations of the complaint who have been dominated by the alleged wrongdoers.","start":1705.759,"stop":1725.568,"duration":19.81},{"text":"The corporation is not shown to have any disability to protect itself or to be captive.","start":1725.568,"stop":1733.2,"duration":7.63},{"text":"And under those circumstances, the California rule is applied as follows, that a -- that in the absence of fraud, bad faith, or domination, the directors of a corporation have the right to decide the questions involved in the administration of that corporation including specifically the question of whether to file a particular lawsuit.","start":1733.2,"stop":1759.32,"duration":26.12}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Williams, well I'm struggling to what you've just said that the causes and the diversity case that the federal court is controlled by the state law as to what constitutes control under the questions that arise in -- in state litigation.","start":1759.32,"stop":1775.508,"duration":16.19}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"It's not --","start":1775.508,"stop":1775.907,"duration":0.4}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"In other words, just -- suppose the California Supreme Court ruled as a matter of law that 15% of stockholding isn't enough to give you control.","start":1775.907,"stop":1785.835,"duration":9.93},{"text":"Would that determine the question of realigning the party?","start":1785.835,"stop":1788.852,"duration":3.02}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":1788.852,"stop":1789.826,"duration":0.97},{"text":"I don't say --","start":1789.826,"stop":1789.943,"duration":0.12}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That's a federal question.","start":1789.943,"stop":1790.989,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"That's a federal question.","start":1790.989,"stop":1791.991,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That's a question of -- in my point of view, essentially a question of fact to be determined by the District Court.","start":1791.991,"stop":1797.798,"duration":5.81}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Absolutely, Your Honor.","start":1797.798,"stop":1798.445,"duration":0.65}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Under California or any other state law has nothing to do with it.","start":1798.445,"stop":1801.425,"duration":2.98}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Absolutely.","start":1801.425,"stop":1802.096,"duration":0.67},{"text":"The -- the state law has no -- the State of California has no authority to limit or control the federal court in determining its own jurisdiction.","start":1802.096,"stop":1811.2,"duration":9.1}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"California law comes into play after the -- if diversity is established --","start":1811.2,"stop":1815.766,"duration":4.57}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1815.766,"stop":1816.301,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- and you go to the merits of a suit.","start":1816.301,"stop":1817.769,"duration":1.47}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1817.769,"stop":1818.634,"duration":0.87},{"text":"The point I'm trying to make is this, not that this Court is bound by California law because that is the last thing I would suggest.","start":1818.634,"stop":1825.632,"duration":7},{"text":"It is this, that this rule, in the application of this rule in this case is in conformity with the substantive rule involving California.","start":1825.632,"stop":1837.957,"duration":12.33}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, why do you have to so?","start":1837.957,"stop":1839.069,"duration":1.11},{"text":"It's simply confusing if I may --","start":1839.069,"stop":1840.39,"duration":1.32}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it may be.","start":1840.39,"stop":1841.973,"duration":1.58},{"text":"It may be and I -- I have given it because I thought it has some reference to the subject matter.","start":1841.973,"stop":1848.428,"duration":6.46},{"text":"And if I am wrong, well, I have wasted my time.","start":1848.428,"stop":1851.941,"duration":3.51},{"text":"Now, I know that there are many cases and they've been discussed in the brief and I don't intend to discuss them.","start":1851.941,"stop":1859.783,"duration":7.84},{"text":"There are many cases particularly in the -- in the various Courts of Appeal and in the District Courts where there is -- apparent to me, a great deal of confusion of thought on the question of -- of what is the true rule.","start":1859.783,"stop":1874.058,"duration":14.28},{"text":"But we again state and -- and this is the very gist of my argument that so far as the law now stands in the United States, it has been determined by the Supreme Court of the United States starting here with some of the earlier cases or removal cases in the Ketchum against Pacific.","start":1874.058,"stop":1895.193,"duration":21.13},{"text":"It has been the -- the basic proposition that parties will arraign.","start":1895.193,"stop":1902.189,"duration":7},{"text":"It'd be aligned in accordance with their real interest was very fully covered in the Indianapolis against Chase National Bank.","start":1902.189,"stop":1911.654,"duration":9.46},{"text":"And then, we get down to the specific cases and I -- I assert to this Court, the Doctor against Harrington, Venner against the Great Northern and Koster against the Lumbermens are the cases which determined the law in -- in the United States at this time.","start":1911.654,"stop":1929.343,"duration":17.69},{"text":"And if -- if that is not the law, if it is not the law that in all cases of stockholders to remedy suits, the corporation will be aligned as a plaintiff because it is the entity for whose benefit the action is being brought, except when it is under disability to defend itself.","start":1929.343,"stop":1955.941,"duration":26.6}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"It's not enough to show that the arrangement that the board of directors that are favor of it be detrimental to the corporation.","start":1955.941,"stop":1963.465,"duration":7.52},{"text":"It will be damaging to it, in the opinion of the stockholder as --","start":1963.465,"stop":1966.416,"duration":2.95}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no, if it's a difference of opinion in the absence of fraud or bad faith or other disability, if it's a mere difference of opinion, the board of directors have a right to do -- to have a -- have good judgment or a bad judgment in reference to that.","start":1966.416,"stop":1981.811,"duration":15.39}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"In fact, it's their own mistake in having their own corporation.","start":1981.811,"stop":1984.824,"duration":3.01}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1984.824,"stop":1985.406,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, why doesn't that go to the merits instead of jurisdiction?","start":1985.406,"stop":1988.251,"duration":2.85}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it goes to the merits and to jurisdiction.","start":1988.251,"stop":1990.904,"duration":2.65}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't see where --","start":1990.904,"stop":1991.542,"duration":0.64}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I can't -- I can't see in this case any point of jurisdiction, any question of fact in connection with jurisdiction that in this particular case, doesn't also go to the merits.","start":1991.542,"stop":2008.118,"duration":16.58},{"text":"It just happens because --","start":2008.118,"stop":2008.62,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I don't know of this particular case, if a stockholder says that X owns a corporation, $100,000.","start":2008.62,"stop":2016.026,"duration":7.41}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2016.026,"stop":2017.267,"duration":1.24}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And the stockholder writes to the corporation, “Will you please sue X for $100,000?”","start":2017.267,"stop":2023.309,"duration":6.04}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2023.309,"stop":2025.144,"duration":1.84}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And the -- the secretary of the corporation or their lawyer writes to the stockholder.","start":2025.144,"stop":2030.594,"duration":5.45},{"text":"“He ought to have the 47th receipt and I'm ought -- I'm instructed to inform you the corporation has decided not to bring suit against X.”","start":2030.594,"stop":2039.957,"duration":9.36},{"text":"Suppose you have that, nothing more.","start":2039.957,"stop":2041.236,"duration":1.28}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, nothing more.","start":2041.236,"stop":2042.469,"duration":1.23}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What would you do in that case?","start":2042.469,"stop":2043.732,"duration":1.26}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I say that if you have not that and nothing more, the corporation should be aligned as a plaintiff.","start":2043.732,"stop":2048.46,"duration":4.73}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And that has nothing to do whether indeed X owes a $100,000 to the corporation.","start":2048.46,"stop":2052.302,"duration":3.84}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":2052.302,"stop":2052.815,"duration":0.51},{"text":"As a matter of fact, X might owe $100,000.","start":2052.815,"stop":2054.891,"duration":2.08}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Or he might not.","start":2054.891,"stop":2055.82,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2055.82,"stop":2056.351,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And that has nothing to do where you put the corporation in that litigation.","start":2056.351,"stop":2059.51,"duration":3.16}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"In that litigation in -- in our judgment under these authorities.","start":2059.51,"stop":2063.481,"duration":3.97},{"text":"Now, I -- I --","start":2063.481,"stop":2063.589,"duration":0.11}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"What do -- what do you do with Chicago against Mills?","start":2063.589,"stop":2066.771,"duration":3.18}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I think Chicago against Mills is very readily distinguishable because in Chicago against Mills, it was an ultra vires case in which it was claimed that the act of the corporation was ultra vires.","start":2066.771,"stop":2079.32,"duration":12.55},{"text":"In all of those ultra vires cases, the stockholder has a cause of action in his own right in which he asked for a judgment against the corporation.","start":2079.32,"stop":2090.362,"duration":11.04},{"text":"To the effect of this shall be enjoined from committing the ultra vires act.","start":2090.362,"stop":2094.498,"duration":4.14},{"text":"So that the corporation is of necessity joined as a party defendant because some -- some relief is asked for against the corporation which is not true in the derivative case.","start":2094.498,"stop":2106.944,"duration":12.45}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That's the way the income tax case was -- and later on the federal law and the corporation is asked.","start":2106.944,"stop":2114.027,"duration":7.08},{"text":"If the stockholder says that you mustn't pay this tax, not that I'm enforcing some claim that you have.","start":2114.027,"stop":2121.58,"duration":7.55}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2121.58,"stop":2122.067,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But if the claim that I had against you not will be guilty of devastated of the State.","start":2122.067,"stop":2126.842,"duration":4.78}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":2126.842,"stop":2127.652,"duration":0.81},{"text":"And in those cases in my judgment are completely distinguishable from this case.","start":2127.652,"stop":2131.873,"duration":4.22},{"text":"Now I --","start":2131.873,"stop":2132.494,"duration":0.62}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"So, what is the ground here basically, a fraud charged against it, the -- to make -- be made the basis for setting aside this contract between Warner Brothers and the United?","start":2132.494,"stop":2150.055,"duration":17.56}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"It is a license that Harry Warner and Jack Warner device a scheme of causing the corporation to enter into a contract with the son-in-law of Harry Warner by which the son-in-law would be at risk in the contract and the corporation would be most of its money.","start":2150.055,"stop":2169.734,"duration":19.68},{"text":"And -- and that they forced the board of directors who may dominated and controlled to approve that contract.","start":2169.734,"stop":2178.385,"duration":8.65}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"And what's the difference between that issue and the issue that you say would require to be proven to show that the -- the party should be realized?","start":2178.385,"stop":2190.144,"duration":11.76}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"No difference.","start":2190.144,"stop":2191.002,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"None?","start":2191.002,"stop":2191.502,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I think that -- I think in this case, the question of jurisdiction, the question of the right of the stockholder to bring any action at all as -- as set forth in Rule 23 (b) and the merits of the case are quite extensive.","start":2191.502,"stop":2210.196,"duration":18.69},{"text":"Now, I noticed from the -- it's last year that I have used the time which I allow it to myself because Mr. Schwab who speaks for other defendants want some time.","start":2210.196,"stop":2220.281,"duration":10.09},{"text":"I thank Your Honors for your help, thank you.","start":2220.281,"stop":2231.581,"duration":11.3}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Schwab.","start":2231.581,"stop":2233.478,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and members of the Court.","start":2233.478,"stop":2238.416,"duration":4.94},{"text":"Perhaps to continue on the same line for a moment and bring into a little clearer focus what happened in this trial, I don't quite agree that in every instance, the issue of the merits is relevant to the issue of control or antagonism or to the issue of disability of the corporation.","start":2238.416,"stop":2260.302,"duration":21.89},{"text":"It so happened that in the instance given by Mr. Justice Frankfurter, it may not be relevant for the Court to inquire whether or not the promissory note was valid, whether or not the corporation owed it.","start":2260.302,"stop":2275.432,"duration":15.13},{"text":"However, in this case, Judge Mathes, in an effort to lean over backwards and to accept every possible inquiry into the facts relevant to jurisdiction, listened to evidence not only as to the freedom of action of these directors, but also looked at the contract.","start":2275.432,"stop":2298.627,"duration":23.2},{"text":"Now, it is true and this is partially an answer to your inquiry, Mr. Justice Black.","start":2298.627,"stop":2304.212,"duration":5.59},{"text":"It is true that the contract might be circumstantial evidence that the directors were dominated or acted fraudulently.","start":2304.212,"stop":2315.269,"duration":11.06},{"text":"That is the relevance, only, the only relevance of the contract in this situation.","start":2315.269,"stop":2320.199,"duration":4.93},{"text":"So, in the case of Mr. Justice Frankfurter's inquiry, it is possible that if a plaintiff comes in and says, “The corporation refuses to sue on $100,000 promissory note.”","start":2320.199,"stop":2330.51,"duration":10.31},{"text":"The evidence may be as follows, the directors may take the stand and say, “We don't think it's collectible.”","start":2330.51,"stop":2336.132,"duration":5.62},{"text":"They may say, “We don't think we have a good cause of action.”","start":2336.132,"stop":2339.108,"duration":2.98},{"text":"Or they may say, “We have appraised this and in our opinion, the corporation would waste its money suing.”","start":2339.108,"stop":2344.931,"duration":5.82},{"text":"Now whether or not -- whether or not the promissory note is valid would only be circumstantial evidence to show that the directors were or were not acting fraudulently.","start":2344.931,"stop":2355.228,"duration":10.3},{"text":"That is all.","start":2355.228,"stop":2356.41,"duration":1.18},{"text":"Now, in this case, Judge Mathes need not to have inquire into this contract.","start":2356.41,"stop":2361.137,"duration":4.73},{"text":"The fact of the matter is that he opened the door that we had an unlimited trial, that this case went 15 days or more, that this case involved a hundred and some exhibits that this contract was shown and the testimony of the executive vice president to be a contract from which Warner Brothers would derived over a $11 million in profits, that this contract were shown not to be an unusual transaction, but one of steady current of business transaction.","start":2361.137,"stop":2390.111,"duration":28.97}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"You're saying that under the evidence, it was stipulated not enough to prove the allegations they made of course.","start":2390.111,"stop":2397.35,"duration":7.24},{"text":"But suppose the allegations had been proven, just as they made them or the illegality and so forth, would that have the matter it require to realign with the party?","start":2397.35,"stop":2406.876,"duration":9.53}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"If the evidence had shown that these directors were acting fraudulently and under domination, then this corporation would not have been acting in its best interest.","start":2406.876,"stop":2418.432,"duration":11.56}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if they had shown exactly what the alleged in the complaint as a ground to set it aside, would that have required the realignment of them as a party defendant?","start":2418.432,"stop":2426.781,"duration":8.35}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"I would say that it would, but this Court found after the trial court found and the Circuit Court examined the record and found that there was no fraud and that there was no domination.","start":2426.781,"stop":2441.075,"duration":14.29},{"text":"And that therefore, this corporation, Warner Brothers, was acting in its own best interest even though it was in disagreement with the plaintiff over whether this suit should be brought.","start":2441.075,"stop":2450.645,"duration":9.57}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"And even though this record might have a dual interest, that's not enough.","start":2450.645,"stop":2454.06,"duration":3.41}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it might be enough, Your Honor.","start":2454.06,"stop":2456.862,"duration":2.8},{"text":"But in this case, Judge Mathes found after a protracted trial that it was not enough.","start":2456.862,"stop":2464.003,"duration":7.14},{"text":"He listened to the evidence.","start":2464.003,"stop":2465.961,"duration":1.96},{"text":"Mr. Levy had an unlimited opportunity.","start":2465.961,"stop":2468.33,"duration":2.37},{"text":"As a matter of fact, December 15th of this year, we will be nine years in this litigation.","start":2468.33,"stop":2473.263,"duration":4.93},{"text":"And may I point out that we didn't file a single delaying tactic.","start":2473.263,"stop":2477.2,"duration":3.94},{"text":"We've didn't demur.","start":2477.2,"stop":2478.253,"duration":1.05},{"text":"We didn't do anything.","start":2478.253,"stop":2479.862,"duration":1.61},{"text":"As a matter of fact, we would like to come to trial whether it's before the federal court, the state court or even a justice of the peace.","start":2479.862,"stop":2486.851,"duration":6.99},{"text":"We feel our -- we feel we have the right with the matter.","start":2486.851,"stop":2489.875,"duration":3.02}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"May I ask you some quote on that question?","start":2489.875,"stop":2491.546,"duration":1.67}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2491.546,"stop":2493.845,"duration":2.3}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I understood you to say he had an unlimited opportunity.","start":2493.845,"stop":2496.827,"duration":2.98}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":2496.827,"stop":2498.712,"duration":1.88}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"He have that when the issues were limited if -- if the issue was really tried out on the basis of showing or giving him a chance to prove the fraud he alleged which was made of realignment.","start":2498.712,"stop":2512.951,"duration":14.24},{"text":"Why should it have been limited to the question of jurisdiction?","start":2512.951,"stop":2516.832,"duration":3.88}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"Because, Your Honor, as is necessary and this Court has frequently said, “The federal court should examine the issue of jurisdiction.”","start":2516.832,"stop":2526.531,"duration":9.7},{"text":"And on the issue of --","start":2526.531,"stop":2527.462,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"To choose being its in depth, he had the right to and yes, he had a right to offer up all evidence such in the merits of his claim and if --","start":2527.462,"stop":2535.791,"duration":8.33}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, may I say that the Court held that if Mr. Levy wanted to introduce the contract and examine whether it appeared fair, a circumstantial evidence.","start":2535.791,"stop":2545.621,"duration":9.83},{"text":"Now, I'm paraphrasing the meaning of the Court's position that here was evidence by the directors as to their conduct.","start":2545.621,"stop":2552.667,"duration":7.05},{"text":"Here was all kinds of evidence that they were fair and free.","start":2552.667,"stop":2556.191,"duration":3.52},{"text":"This is my epitomization of it.","start":2556.191,"stop":2558.044,"duration":1.85},{"text":"They were not acting under domination.","start":2558.044,"stop":2559.82,"duration":1.78},{"text":"They were not acting under fraud.","start":2559.82,"stop":2561.59,"duration":1.77},{"text":"They were fair and free.","start":2561.59,"stop":2563.359,"duration":1.77},{"text":"Now, Mr. Levy says, \"That isn't enough.","start":2563.359,"stop":2565.685,"duration":2.33},{"text":"I want to show this contract.","start":2565.685,"stop":2567.537,"duration":1.85},{"text":"I want to show by implication or innuendo that something is wrong here that the Court hasn't seen.\"","start":2567.537,"stop":2573.459,"duration":5.92},{"text":"So, the Court said, “Introduce the contract.”","start":2573.459,"stop":2575.59,"duration":2.13},{"text":"And as a matter of fact, we introduced a dozen other contract of similar nature that Warner Brothers had entered into.","start":2575.59,"stop":2581.411,"duration":5.82},{"text":"This was no odd contract.","start":2581.411,"stop":2583.437,"duration":2.03},{"text":"This was a course of business and it so happened that this was a desirable course of business and this -- this endeavor to introduce nepotism under these cases, is to me beside the point.","start":2583.437,"stop":2596.09,"duration":12.65},{"text":"This is strictly a case of federal jurisdiction, and the Court held a fair trial on federal jurisdiction.","start":2596.09,"stop":2601.783,"duration":5.69},{"text":"And if anything, Mr. Justice Black, the Court went too far in my opinion in permitting everything into the record that could possibly touch upon the issue of domination or control or basically, disability.","start":2601.783,"stop":2612.997,"duration":11.21}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Mr. Schwab, if the Court had arrived at the opposite conclusion and had found that the corporation should have been realigned as a party defendant, do I understand from what you and Mr. Williams have said that on this record, automatically then, there would have been a judgment on the merits for the plaintiff?","start":2612.997,"stop":2631.535,"duration":18.54}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":2631.535,"stop":2632.179,"duration":0.64},{"text":"Then, the Court would have been governed under Erie versus Tompkins by the rule of California.","start":2632.179,"stop":2636.796,"duration":4.62},{"text":"And then, Mr. Levy might have decided he wanted 10 more days of evidence.","start":2636.796,"stop":2640.193,"duration":3.4},{"text":"I don't know.","start":2640.193,"stop":2641.074,"duration":0.88},{"text":"He had a free hand here and incidentally --","start":2641.074,"stop":2644.113,"duration":3.04}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then -- then, that's now to tell us then that there has not been a complete trial on merits.","start":2644.113,"stop":2648.915,"duration":4.8}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"There has not been a complete trial on the merits.","start":2648.915,"stop":2651.221,"duration":2.31},{"text":"What I've said is there has been a complete and unlimited trial on issue of jurisdiction.","start":2651.221,"stop":2655.989,"duration":4.77},{"text":"And that issue --","start":2655.989,"stop":2656.204,"duration":0.22}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I thought Mr. Williams told us earlier that the evidence was actually that would which would constitute a complete (Voice Overlap) --","start":2656.204,"stop":2665.28,"duration":9.08}]},{"speakerName":"Oliver B. Schwab","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what Mr. Williams has said is what I started out to say, that the evidence may apply to both issues.","start":2665.28,"stop":2671.505,"duration":6.22},{"text":"In other words, under state law in California as was said here yesterday, the substantive law may be that if the directors act honestly, if they are fair and free, that's the end of it.","start":2671.505,"stop":2683.796,"duration":12.29},{"text":"That's a matter of state substantive law, but it may also be a matter relevant to Doctor and Harrington.","start":2683.796,"stop":2689.96,"duration":6.16},{"text":"Now, what I am saying is that this Court gave the plaintiff unlimited time to prove anything he wanted, directors circumstantial on the issue of whether or not these directors were fair and free.","start":2689.96,"stop":2702.073,"duration":12.11},{"text":"And when he have no more to say, and incidentally, while I was going to -- to -- with respect to Mr. Levy's remark that I have no further evidence to offer under those circumstances, that related to Mr. William's statement.","start":2702.073,"stop":2715.723,"duration":13.65},{"text":"In other words, Mr. Levy said, \"Well, maybe, I want to examine.","start":2715.723,"stop":2718.945,"duration":3.22},{"text":"Maybe, I thought of whether I should examine some of the directors.\"","start":2718.945,"stop":2721.705,"duration":2.76},{"text":"Incidentally, he had any period of time to do that.","start":2721.705,"stop":2724.836,"duration":3.13},{"text":"The depositions were taken.","start":2724.836,"stop":2726.134,"duration":1.3},{"text":"He could have had them in Court.","start":2726.134,"stop":2727.335,"duration":1.2},{"text":"This was up to his freewill.","start":2727.335,"stop":2729.034,"duration":1.7},{"text":"Now, the last day after 15 days of trial and he wasn't cut off, this Court I think would have gone on for 10 more days.","start":2729.034,"stop":2736.025,"duration":6.99},{"text":"He said, \"Well, maybe I should examine.\"","start":2736.025,"stop":2737.758,"duration":1.73},{"text":"Then, Mr. William said, \"Look, it is our position that the corporation considers this a fair contract, and therefore, where the corporation wouldn't have sued because it considered it a fair and good contract.\"","start":2737.758,"stop":2748.824,"duration":11.07},{"text":"Then, Mr. Levy said, \"Well, under those circumstances, that is all.\"","start":2748.824,"stop":2751.996,"duration":3.17},{"text":"In other words, he had his full opportunity to try this issue of jurisdiction and to attempt to show under Doctor versus Harrington that the corporation was in antagonistic hand and after that trial, he did.","start":2751.996,"stop":2764.276,"duration":12.28},{"text":"Now, -- and that, after that trial, the Court held that he had not proved that the corporation was disabled and therefore the Court lack federal jurisdiction.","start":2764.276,"stop":2773.702,"duration":9.43},{"text":"I want to add this by way of illuminating background to show how clearly this is a case strictly of federal jurisdiction.","start":2773.702,"stop":2780.894,"duration":7.19},{"text":"This controversy started by suit in New York in 1948.","start":2780.894,"stop":2785.653,"duration":4.76},{"text":"These are matters of judicial notice.","start":2785.653,"stop":2787.433,"duration":1.78},{"text":"Immediately after that, there were piggyback bases, almost Chinese copies.","start":2787.433,"stop":2791.71,"duration":4.28},{"text":"There were 19 cases filed in New York.","start":2791.71,"stop":2794.897,"duration":3.19},{"text":"There were nine or ten of them in the state court, nine in the Federal Court.","start":2794.897,"stop":2798.538,"duration":3.64},{"text":"It was because of the bond rule and the case of Cohen versus Beneficial Loan that the plaintiff's attorneys in New York forwarded the cases to California and there were two, or three, or four or five, more.","start":2798.538,"stop":2809.668,"duration":11.13},{"text":"Now, some of the state courses in -- courts in New York are -- the cases are still pending.","start":2809.668,"stop":2814.033,"duration":4.36},{"text":"This is no question whether plaintiff doesn't have a form.","start":2814.033,"stop":2816.78,"duration":2.75},{"text":"He's not barred by the statute of limitations.","start":2816.78,"stop":2819.176,"duration":2.4},{"text":"He is trying to elect the federal court.","start":2819.176,"stop":2821.695,"duration":2.52},{"text":"He is trying to circumvent the rule of Doctor versus Harrington.","start":2821.695,"stop":2824.824,"duration":3.13},{"text":"The only issue here is that whether he has or hasn't the cause of action.","start":2824.824,"stop":2828.326,"duration":3.5},{"text":"We think he has it and we think that under California law, he'd be held not to have under the substantive law, but the fact to the matter is that the federal jurisdiction in this case has not been proven.","start":2828.326,"stop":2841.746,"duration":13.42},{"text":"I -- I had some other things to say on this but I'm afraid I -- I have ran out.","start":2841.746,"stop":2846.98,"duration":5.23},{"text":"Thank you.","start":2846.98,"stop":2849.706,"duration":2.73}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Levy.","start":2849.706,"stop":2859.802,"duration":10.1}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Justice Black asked the question whether there had been a complete trial on the merits.","start":2859.802,"stop":2865.343,"duration":5.54},{"text":"May I quote in this part?","start":2865.343,"stop":2867.696,"duration":2.35},{"text":"I refer the Court to page 572, first of the record in which I say, \"I am just wondering, Your Honor, the reason why -- the reason why I say there maybe some occasion is this.","start":2867.696,"stop":2882.272,"duration":14.58},{"text":"We are trying, as I understand, limited issues here now and this applies to both this witness and the witness, Mr. Friedman who preceded him and so forth.\"","start":2882.272,"stop":2893.122,"duration":10.85},{"text":"And the Court says, \"Mr. Levy, you may need them tomorrow,\" meaning, the witnesses that we were talking about.","start":2893.122,"stop":2898.508,"duration":5.39},{"text":"“I will ask them to remain until tomorrow.","start":2898.508,"stop":2900.83,"duration":2.32},{"text":"I hope we can reach a conclusion of the evidence tomorrow on this matter.”","start":2900.83,"stop":2904.304,"duration":3.47},{"text":"Mr. Levy, “On the issues that we are trying now, Your Honor?","start":2904.304,"stop":2907.454,"duration":3.15},{"text":"The Court, \"On the issues, yes.","start":2907.454,"stop":2910.101,"duration":2.65},{"text":"On the issue as to jurisdiction and the issue as to the statute of limitations.”","start":2910.101,"stop":2914.792,"duration":4.69},{"text":"Now, on page 583 of the record, the Court says, \"Do both sides rest on the issues as to jurisdiction latches or limitation?\"","start":2914.792,"stop":2927.404,"duration":12.61},{"text":"Mr. Williams, \"Yes, Your Honor.\"","start":2927.404,"stop":2929.201,"duration":1.8},{"text":"Mr. Levy, \"Yes, Your Honor.\"","start":2929.201,"stop":2930.648,"duration":1.45},{"text":"The Court, \"If we take up the case further on the merits, it will be some time -- it would be some time in July, the last half of July or in the Fall.\"","start":2930.648,"stop":2943.55,"duration":12.9},{"text":"Now, if that isn't in itself sufficient, we go to page 586 --","start":2943.55,"stop":2948.923,"duration":5.37}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"What was that other page, 583 did --","start":2948.923,"stop":2951.083,"duration":2.16}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"583, Your Honor.","start":2951.083,"stop":2952.26,"duration":1.18}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"583.","start":2952.26,"stop":2953.398,"duration":1.14}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Is it your view, Mr. Levy that when a Court in a -- in this kind of a diversity case that's confronted with the problem appropriately raised as to the side on which the corporation whose claim is being pressed by a stockholder?","start":2953.398,"stop":2974.56,"duration":21.16},{"text":"When the District Court is confronted with that question, must we go to the merits of the corporate claim which the stockholder is seeking to enforce?","start":2974.56,"stop":2984.495,"duration":9.93}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor, he need not.","start":2984.495,"stop":2985.324,"duration":0.83}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Then what is the point of what you're now stating?","start":2985.324,"stop":2987.523,"duration":2.2}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"All that he need do is this.","start":2987.523,"stop":2990.355,"duration":2.83},{"text":"The Court -- Mr. Chief Justice, wait, laid down the rule way back in Pacific Railroad against Ketchum that when a question of jurisdiction arises at the threshold, then it should arise right at the threshold.","start":2990.355,"stop":3003.788,"duration":13.43},{"text":"The Court will look into the matter and determine what kind of a case is this.","start":3003.788,"stop":3009.894,"duration":6.11},{"text":"Let's see what this is about and the next thing that he must do --","start":3009.894,"stop":3012.913,"duration":3.02}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) merely as to pursue that the Court has to adjudicate --","start":3012.913,"stop":3016.806,"duration":3.89}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":3016.806,"stop":3017.232,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- whether or not there is a claim?","start":3017.232,"stop":3018.776,"duration":1.54}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":3018.776,"stop":3019.49,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what I can -- that's what to me, means the term -- the merits mean.","start":3019.49,"stop":3023.314,"duration":3.82}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":3023.314,"stop":3024.518,"duration":1.2},{"text":"In other words, the Court does not adjudicate at that point whether he has the power to hear and determine as a federal court what this case is all about and to decide either in the plaintiff -- for the plaintiff or for the defendant.","start":3024.518,"stop":3037.269,"duration":12.75},{"text":"All he has called upon to do under Chief Justice Waite's rule was this.","start":3037.269,"stop":3042.234,"duration":4.97},{"text":"Let me see what this case is about and then let me see who belongs on one side and who belongs on the other side.","start":3042.234,"stop":3050.028,"duration":7.79},{"text":"Who says this and who says that.","start":3050.028,"stop":3051.947,"duration":1.92},{"text":"Now, according to your own -- to Your Honor's own rule laid down in Indianapolis case.","start":3051.947,"stop":3057.551,"duration":5.6},{"text":"You said that in that case that Chase and in the -- in Indianapolis were partners in litigation.","start":3057.551,"stop":3065.035,"duration":7.48},{"text":"Now, the facts in this case even under these findings show that these two people -- that is the -- the Warner Brothers, the individual defendants and the corporation here were partners in litigation.","start":3065.035,"stop":3079.181,"duration":14.15}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But that has nothing to do with adjudicating the question whether ultimately --","start":3079.181,"stop":3083.834,"duration":4.65}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":3083.834,"stop":3084.129,"duration":0.3}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- these defendants were fraudulent.","start":3084.129,"stop":3085.906,"duration":1.78}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":3085.906,"stop":3086.439,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"All right.","start":3086.439,"stop":3086.562,"duration":0.12}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"They had nothing to do with that at all.","start":3086.562,"stop":3088.529,"duration":1.97}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"If for example upheld there is no jurisdiction, you could go ahead and practice status out of the state court?","start":3088.529,"stop":3094.092,"duration":5.56}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":3094.092,"stop":3095.436,"duration":1.34},{"text":"And the Court so held in this case.","start":3095.436,"stop":3097.381,"duration":1.94},{"text":"Whatever we found here is not on the merits and he -- he had it in his opinion.Of course, if the complainant in this case has to go to the state court, he'll certainly will -- and never practically won't prevail if the statute of limitation is going to be a -- become a bar to them.","start":3097.381,"stop":3114.146,"duration":16.77}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But the fact that the statute of limitations might have run because you chose -- because a litigant chooses to go to the federal court, there's no reason for finding their federal jurisdiction.","start":3114.146,"stop":3123.702,"duration":9.56}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":3123.702,"stop":3124.404,"duration":0.7}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"All right.","start":3124.404,"stop":3124.451,"duration":0.05}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Absolutely not.","start":3124.451,"stop":3125.487,"duration":1.04}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, let me ask you this question.","start":3125.487,"stop":3126.599,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":3126.599,"stop":3128.012,"duration":1.41}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose your adversary is right on what he claimed has to be established in order to realign the target, how could you decide it in this case without deciding the merits of your action?","start":3128.012,"stop":3140.303,"duration":12.29}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"He couldn't.","start":3140.303,"stop":3141.908,"duration":1.61}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What you are saying is that you do not have to try the merits.","start":3141.908,"stop":3145.112,"duration":3.2}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":3145.112,"stop":3145.313,"duration":0.2}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"So, you say that that can't be wrong.","start":3145.313,"stop":3148.023,"duration":2.71}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":3148.023,"stop":3148.397,"duration":0.37}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"And that your test is right and that under your test that the -- entitled for him to try the case.","start":3148.397,"stop":3154.229,"duration":5.83}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":3154.229,"stop":3154.746,"duration":0.52},{"text":"And I'll give Your Honor and an answer to Mr. Justice Brennan's question, the test -- Your Honor asked me that yesterday and the test has been very, very nicely and I believe adequately and justly stated by Judge Lanning in New Jersey in the case of Groel against the Electric Company.","start":3154.746,"stop":3175.617,"duration":20.87},{"text":"He said this.","start":3175.617,"stop":3177.615,"duration":2},{"text":"And may I read from the 21 of my brief?","start":3177.615,"stop":3180.4,"duration":2.79},{"text":"The Groel case suit problem -- this is my brief in the Court of Appeals, Your Honors.","start":3180.4,"stop":3185.162,"duration":4.76},{"text":"The Groel case suit problem was decided some 25 years after the removal cases.","start":3185.162,"stop":3190.047,"duration":4.89},{"text":"In that case, the complainant stopped although a citizen of New Jersey had instituted a derivative suit in the New Jersey Court of Chancery, the defendant's name with his corporation, a New Jersey Company and the Pennsylvania Corporation.","start":3190.047,"stop":3203.554,"duration":13.51},{"text":"The case had been removed from the state court to the federal District Court of New Jersey.","start":3203.554,"stop":3208.563,"duration":5.01},{"text":"Plaintiff stopped all the move to remand on the ground that both he --","start":3208.563,"stop":3214.081,"duration":5.52}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You may finish that short quotation.","start":3214.081,"stop":3216.031,"duration":1.95}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"-- and the defendant, New Jersey Corporation were citizens of New Jersey.","start":3216.031,"stop":3220.64,"duration":4.61},{"text":"In our position to the motion, it was contended that since the stockholder was urging, not his, but to the corporation's cause of action which has been the contention throughout here, but that is controlling.","start":3220.64,"stop":3233.815,"duration":13.18},{"text":"The federal court should view the stockholder's corporation as a plaintiff and realign it with the complainant, thus bringing about diversity.","start":3233.815,"stop":3243.583,"duration":9.77},{"text":"The Court declines to do so and said on page 263, quote, \"This contention has seem to necessitate before going to review of the authorities and Judge Lanning really made a review of the authorities.\"","start":3243.583,"stop":3257.068,"duration":13.49},{"text":"The rule deduced from them is that, in astute in equity instituted by a stockholder in his own name, but upon a right of action existing in his corporation, the stockholder's corporation will be aligned with the defendant's whenever the officers or persons controlling the corporation are shown to be opposed to the object sought by the complaining stockholder.","start":3257.068,"stop":3285.649,"duration":28.58},{"text":"And that when such opposition does not appear, the stockholder's corporation will be aligned with the complainant in the suit, and this case was cited with approval in Venner against the Great Northern.","start":3285.649,"stop":3298.019,"duration":12.37}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean to say that if the rule that you're offering, that whenever a -- whenever a stockholder seeks to enforce a claim which runs to the corporation in his view and he asked the corporation to sue and the corporation said, \"We're very sorry.","start":3298.019,"stop":3317.669,"duration":19.65},{"text":"We do not think it is desirable to sue.","start":3317.669,"stop":3321.111,"duration":3.44},{"text":"We do not think we can win in this case.","start":3321.111,"stop":3324.379,"duration":3.27},{"text":"Yours truly.\"","start":3324.379,"stop":3325.37,"duration":0.99},{"text":"That at once aligned him with the defendant?","start":3325.37,"stop":3329.212,"duration":3.84}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":3329.212,"stop":3329.889,"duration":0.68},{"text":"I do not.","start":3329.889,"stop":3330.938,"duration":1.05},{"text":"When we say what --","start":3330.938,"stop":3331.127,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I don't understand what -- the reading of that is opposed.","start":3331.127,"stop":3335.369,"duration":4.24}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"May I explain it then, Your Honor?","start":3335.369,"stop":3336.619,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Certainly.","start":3336.619,"stop":3337.041,"duration":0.42}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Judge Lanning meant this.","start":3337.041,"stop":3339.009,"duration":1.97},{"text":"He says when the corporation -- when the directorate of a corporation evinces and makes evident an attitude that is opposed not to the stockholder, because he wears a red tie for example, nothing personal about it.","start":3339.009,"stop":3354.316,"duration":15.31},{"text":"But when it is opposed to what he stands in Court and condense for, when the directorate of the corporation is opposed to that, then it -- the corporation, the -- this directorate is antagonistic to the -- to the -- to the stockholder's claim.","start":3354.316,"stop":3374.307,"duration":19.99},{"text":"And the corporation is in antagonistic hands because the point is this, that in this case, the directors were unanimous.","start":3374.307,"stop":3381.964,"duration":7.66}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not talking about this case.","start":3381.964,"stop":3383.26,"duration":1.3},{"text":"I want a proof.","start":3383.26,"stop":3383.629,"duration":0.37}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"In any case.","start":3383.629,"stop":3384.562,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Are there plaintiffs stockholders, right?So, there, in courteous letter and encloses a very strong opinion from his lawyer saying, \"I've studied the authority and I think the corporation has a good cause of action.\"","start":3384.562,"stop":3398.25,"duration":13.69},{"text":"And that is sent to the secretary to whom service is sent of corporation X.","start":3398.25,"stop":3404.207,"duration":5.96},{"text":"And corporation X sends that on to its general counsel and the general counsel send back an opinion saying, \"I think the opinion of my respected brother at the bar is -- is not in all that, but I think he has overlooked some recent tendency, the Supreme Court decisions.","start":3404.207,"stop":3423.973,"duration":19.77},{"text":"I think the chances of recovery are very remote.","start":3423.973,"stop":3427.074,"duration":3.1},{"text":"This will be a long going out litigation.","start":3427.074,"stop":3429.562,"duration":2.49},{"text":"It will cost a lot of money and incidentally arouse friction and I recommend that the corporation do not make that claim and bring proceeding -- does that on opposition?","start":3429.562,"stop":3442.882,"duration":13.32}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Does Your Honor's premise carry this -- carry this thought as well that the corporation virtually says, \"You may have a point there.”","start":3442.882,"stop":3450.374,"duration":7.49},{"text":"This man -- this corporation may be entitled to get this money, but we think that even though it's entitled to get this money, we don't feel that it's advisable to go ahead and sue because you may not win.","start":3450.374,"stop":3463.185,"duration":12.81},{"text":"Now, I think that under those circumstances, Your Honor, the corporation should be aligned as a defendant for the reason that the directorate is enhanced that is in opposition or inimical to the objects of the stockholder's action which he prepared -- which he is prepared to bring.","start":3463.185,"stop":3480.884,"duration":17.7},{"text":"Now --","start":3480.884,"stop":3481.498,"duration":0.61}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"The corporation in other words isn't entitled to act in good faith on the advise of its counsel.","start":3481.498,"stop":3487.066,"duration":5.57},{"text":"It must take the advice or plaintiff's counsel --","start":3487.066,"stop":3488.901,"duration":1.84}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"In one case, yes, and in one case not.","start":3488.901,"stop":3491.194,"duration":2.29},{"text":"Now, I'll tell, Your Honor, in which case, yes, and in which case, not.","start":3491.194,"stop":3494.304,"duration":3.11},{"text":"If the corporation has a claim, if the stockholder's claim is this, the corporation has a claim against the stranger, the case that you put, Your Honor, put to Mr. Schwab.","start":3494.304,"stop":3504.808,"duration":10.5},{"text":"In other words, the corporate -- the -- the stockholder says, “This corporate -- this stranger owes this corporation a $100,000.00.”","start":3504.808,"stop":3513.121,"duration":8.31},{"text":"And the directorate says, \"Well, no.\"","start":3513.121,"stop":3516.291,"duration":3.17},{"text":"Or maybe -- well, maybe he does and maybe he doesn't.","start":3516.291,"stop":3519.234,"duration":2.94},{"text":"We don't think it's advisable to go ahead.","start":3519.234,"stop":3521.533,"duration":2.3},{"text":"I say that under those circumstances, the stockholder hasn't even got a case for this reason, for this reason because this is a -- a claim of the corporation against the stranger and the directorate can do what it pleases about.","start":3521.533,"stop":3535.652,"duration":14.12},{"text":"In other words, improvidence in such a situation makes no difference and doesn't give the stockholder the right to come into Court.","start":3535.652,"stop":3541.539,"duration":5.89},{"text":"But those cases are distinguishable clearly as Mr. Justice Douglas has pointed out in Pepper against Litton from the case in which a contract is involved between the corporation and its president or his wife or his son-in-law and the case of -- the wife was clearly stated by one of the vice chancellors in Breweries against Nixon in New Jersey.","start":3541.539,"stop":3564.776,"duration":23.24},{"text":"That is a different situation.","start":3564.776,"stop":3566.423,"duration":1.65},{"text":"In those cases, the business judgment rule must yield to the greater rule of undivided loyalty as Mr. Justice Douglas has pointed out in --","start":3566.423,"stop":3575.396,"duration":8.97}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"He's exercising a -- an exercising a business judgment by the corporation is proved disloyal, is that it?","start":3575.396,"stop":3582.605,"duration":7.21}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":3582.605,"stop":3583.326,"duration":0.72},{"text":"I don't say that.","start":3583.326,"stop":3584.487,"duration":1.16},{"text":"Now, that -- that would be --","start":3584.487,"stop":3586.009,"duration":1.52}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What do you say then?","start":3586.009,"stop":3587.227,"duration":1.22}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"I say that where a corporation is engaged in a deal with a son-in-law of the President, and that deal has been arranged by his father-in-law, the president of the company with him and a stockholder comes along and says, \"This is a vehicle by which the (Inaudible) corporate money into the hands of the son-in-law.\"","start":3587.227,"stop":3610.062,"duration":22.84},{"text":"I say under those circumstances, the Court is not bound by the business judgment rule but all the decisions are to the effect that the -- a court of equity will scrutinize the contract carefully for the purpose of determining whether it was in its last analysis fair or unfair, irrespective of whether the board of directors thought it was fair, irrespective of whether they were honest men because even honest men may differ, may be capable of using -- thinking that something is fair which isn't because I'll give Your Honor the simple example.","start":3610.062,"stop":3644.551,"duration":34.49},{"text":"Suppose the board of directors is composed of men who are perfectly honest and perfectly fair, they believe that this president of a corporation should get a million dollars a year.","start":3644.551,"stop":3654.24,"duration":9.69},{"text":"Now, they say in our -- we are -- business judgment rule is exercised right then as to right now, and the stockholder comes along and says, \"Oh, no.","start":3654.24,"stop":3662.801,"duration":8.56},{"text":"This is just ridiculous.","start":3662.801,"stop":3663.952,"duration":1.15},{"text":"This is unreasonable.\"","start":3663.952,"stop":3665.798,"duration":1.85},{"text":"Shall we say that under those circumstances, the stockholder is out, out in the state court or out in a Federal Court?","start":3665.798,"stop":3672.021,"duration":6.22}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That isn't our question.","start":3672.021,"stop":3673.981,"duration":1.96},{"text":"You may be able to get a recovery because the corporation laws of a various state, very enormous, at least they did when I asked you about it which is a long time ago.","start":3673.981,"stop":3684.893,"duration":10.91},{"text":"They're very enormous, for instance whether -- whether a member of the board, whether a director can be a party to a contract of the corporation, whether he's entitled to vote, whether he can be in the room when they take a vote.","start":3684.893,"stop":3698.42,"duration":13.53},{"text":"All those things are questions of substantive law on which the States have their different policies on the basis of which you may or may not recover.","start":3698.42,"stop":3707.583,"duration":9.16}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":3707.583,"stop":3707.728,"duration":0.14}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That has nothing to do with the alignment of party --","start":3707.728,"stop":3710.686,"duration":2.96}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":3710.686,"stop":3711.069,"duration":0.38},{"text":"It has not.","start":3711.069,"stop":3712.185,"duration":1.12},{"text":"And may I make one request, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":3712.185,"stop":3716.187,"duration":4},{"text":"This brief who served my opponent's brief, who served on me the day before I am trained for Washington, from California and I've had absolutely no opportunity of course to reply.","start":3716.187,"stop":3726.179,"duration":9.99},{"text":"May I file -- may I just file with the Court my brief in the Court -- in the Court of Appeals which contains the latest law of the State -- of the State of California on the question not the one cited by my opponent namely Finley against Gareth, but the later case unless Your Honors want to take it down, the case of Kennerson against Burbank 120 Cal.Ap.California Appeals 157 -- 170 in which the law of California is stated to be clearly the law as stated by Mr. Justice Douglas in Pepper against Litton are no different.","start":3726.179,"stop":3764.809,"duration":38.63},{"text":"May I --","start":3764.809,"stop":3765.416,"duration":0.61}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You may file it.","start":3765.416,"stop":3765.823,"duration":0.41}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"-- please file it?","start":3765.823,"stop":3766.754,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3766.754,"stop":3767.452,"duration":0.7}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you, Your Honors.","start":3767.452,"stop":3769.563,"duration":2.11}]}]},{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - March 27, 1957","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren6/oral_argument_audio/13317","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Number 422, Office Employees International Union, Local Number 11, AFL-CIO, Petitioner, versus, National Labor Relations Board.","start":0,"stop":18.01,"duration":18.01},{"text":"Oh, wait a minute, wait a minute, wait a minute.","start":18.01,"stop":21.051,"duration":3.04},{"text":"Well, I beg your pardon.","start":21.051,"stop":21.961,"duration":0.91},{"text":"I -- I just skipped one case result.","start":21.961,"stop":25.491,"duration":3.53},{"text":"Number 316, I'm sorry, Charles B. Smith, as a -- as Special Administrator of the Estate of Edward S. Birn, Deceased, Petitioner, versus Milton Sperling.","start":25.491,"stop":37.829,"duration":12.34},{"text":"Mr. Levy.","start":37.829,"stop":46.309,"duration":8.48}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honors, this case comes here on certiorari for the Ninth Circuit.","start":46.309,"stop":53.069,"duration":6.76},{"text":"In a good many respects, this case is similar to the preceding case.","start":53.069,"stop":61.071,"duration":8},{"text":"In the Swanson case or may I -- at this point interrupt what I was going to say by answering Judge -- Justice Brennan's question directed to Mr. Doyle that in the event a -- the directors of a corporation said to a suing stockholder, there's no use of going on with this thing.","start":61.071,"stop":85.567,"duration":24.5},{"text":"All we can do is try a lawsuit and if they were -- if we get a judgment, it will never be collected whether under said circumstances, the stockholder would be stating the kind of a cause of action that a court of equity or rather would -- would the situation be such as to warrant the alignment of the corporation as a defendant.","start":85.567,"stop":103.677,"duration":18.11},{"text":"I must disagree with Mr. Doyle on that and answer no to that question.","start":103.677,"stop":108.397,"duration":4.72},{"text":"However --","start":108.397,"stop":108.827,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Otherwise, you would always have a realignment --","start":108.827,"stop":110.634,"duration":1.81}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That is --","start":110.634,"stop":110.654,"duration":0.02}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"-- of the corporation on the other side.","start":110.654,"stop":112.104,"duration":1.45}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct, sir.","start":112.104,"stop":113.084,"duration":0.98},{"text":"However, if the issue between the stockholder in that given situation and the corporation with this, the stockholder says, “I don't agree with you.","start":113.084,"stop":122.109,"duration":9.02},{"text":"We will collect this judgment.","start":122.109,"stop":123.869,"duration":1.76},{"text":"I know of assets that this man has.”","start":123.869,"stop":126.739,"duration":2.87},{"text":"Under those circumstances, there was a real disagreement between the stockholder and this corporation.","start":126.739,"stop":132.625,"duration":5.89},{"text":"The corporation being definitely against the stockholder, it assumes an attitude deliberately against him.","start":132.625,"stop":140.224,"duration":7.6},{"text":"And whatever the motives may be of the individual directors will make up this directory.","start":140.224,"stop":146.484,"duration":6.26},{"text":"They, nevertheless, are genuinely oppose to the basic underlying issues that the stockholder races in his charge of wrongdoing against these directors.","start":146.484,"stop":159.356,"duration":12.87}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Levy.","start":159.356,"stop":160.136,"duration":0.78}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":160.136,"stop":160.716,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"On Mr. Justice Brennan's hypothesis, do you think there would be any equity sufficient to enable the plaintiff even to maintain the suit?","start":160.716,"stop":171.216,"duration":10.5}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That depends on whether the plaintiff has alleged in his complaint --","start":171.216,"stop":175.167,"duration":3.95}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Alleged the facts --","start":175.167,"stop":175.527,"duration":0.36}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"-- wrong.","start":175.527,"stop":176.117,"duration":0.59}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"-- alleged -- suppose -- assumed he alleges the facts that Mr. Justice Brennan assumed.","start":176.117,"stop":179.817,"duration":3.7}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I assumed that what Mr. Justice --","start":179.817,"stop":180.957,"duration":1.14}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"It's just a matter of disagreement between the directors and the stockholder.","start":180.957,"stop":184.326,"duration":3.37},{"text":"Is that enough to give the stockholder a right to supplant the directors in their judgment as to whether the suit should be brought?","start":184.326,"stop":189.226,"duration":4.9}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor, but I assume that Mr. -- Mr. Justice Brennan's question assumed that the stockholder had alleged a series of facts which indicated wrongdoing upon the part of these individuals and the directors took this position and they said, “Yes, I guess you're right.","start":189.226,"stop":208.331,"duration":19.1},{"text":"These things are wrong but what's the use of going ahead with this thing?","start":208.331,"stop":211.876,"duration":3.55},{"text":"The corporation alone had spent a lot of money and on the line up, get a judgment against the man who has nothing and cannot collect.”","start":211.876,"stop":219.296,"duration":7.42},{"text":"Now, if the stockholder says, “Well, the disagreement between you and me is this, I disagree on -- on the basic premise that you have made.”","start":219.296,"stop":231.335,"duration":12.04},{"text":"I say this man has a lot of money.","start":231.335,"stop":234.005,"duration":2.67},{"text":"He's got it hidden.","start":234.005,"stop":234.905,"duration":0.9},{"text":"He's got it concealed.","start":234.905,"stop":236.435,"duration":1.53},{"text":"I'll show you how to get it under.","start":236.435,"stop":238.708,"duration":2.27},{"text":"And under those conditions, I say that the -- that the -- we contend that the corporation should be aligned as a defendant because there is an adversity of interest to align such a corporation, to align such directors on the side of the plaintiff to ally them with the plaintiff.","start":238.708,"stop":258.363,"duration":19.66},{"text":"It would create an incongruity of the worst order because in the first place, bare in mind that the directors have no controversy admittedly with these alleged wrongdoers, they say, “We have no controversy with them.”","start":258.363,"stop":270.863,"duration":12.5},{"text":"Taking Mr. Justice Frankfurter's reasoning in the -- in the Indianapolis case.","start":270.863,"stop":276.133,"duration":5.27},{"text":"Why -- how can you take a -- a directorate of a corporation that says, in so many words concededly and admittedly, “We have no quarrel with these defendants.”","start":276.133,"stop":288.203,"duration":12.07},{"text":"We say that what they did was not only proper.","start":288.203,"stop":291.513,"duration":3.31},{"text":"It was not only right.","start":291.513,"stop":293.2,"duration":1.69},{"text":"It was just and the plaintiff hasn't got a case.","start":293.2,"stop":296.49,"duration":3.29},{"text":"Furthermore, in this particular case, in the Warner matter, the defendant corporation joined in an answer with the alleged wrongdoers and it is conceded by counsel in that case that the directors believed that the conduct that the stockholder alleges was wrongful.","start":296.49,"stop":320.751,"duration":24.26},{"text":"It was perfectly proper and just.","start":320.751,"stop":323.331,"duration":2.58},{"text":"And they admit and the fact show that the corporation participated in this wrongful conduct because here, it was a contract made between a corporation, namely, Warner Brothers and Harry Warner's son-in-law.","start":323.331,"stop":335.881,"duration":12.55},{"text":"Now, the corporate -- the stockholder comes along and says, “This was a -- a device and a vehicle by which the money was to be siphoned out of the corporation into the hands of the president's son-in-law.","start":335.881,"stop":348.366,"duration":12.49},{"text":"Now, these things are not unusual.","start":348.366,"stop":350.576,"duration":2.21},{"text":"As I pointed out in my petition for certiorari in this Court, the -- the statistics on the -- on -- on the questions are really astounding.","start":350.576,"stop":367.291,"duration":16.71},{"text":"Here is what the American Institute of Management says as late as May 14th, 1956, I'm quoting now from my petition for certiorari, Your Honors, on page 12.","start":367.291,"stop":378.931,"duration":11.64},{"text":"They say, “Feather-betting occurs as top level management and extends down to the rank performance,” said AIM in the report to its 17,000 members.","start":378.931,"stop":389.667,"duration":10.74},{"text":"And one of the biggest causes of feather-betting is nepotism.","start":389.667,"stop":392.888,"duration":3.22},{"text":"Now, this is what this case is about.","start":392.888,"stop":395.488,"duration":2.6},{"text":"Of course, nepotism, the -- the real connotation probably applies to things governmental, but in its latest connotation, that word has become -- has come to be applied to awkward situations.","start":395.488,"stop":409.678,"duration":14.19},{"text":"In more than -- I -- I quote again in more than half of the 23,000 U.S. companies, AIM studied and executive and put his sons, cousins and brothers even an assortment of relatives on the payroll.","start":409.678,"stop":422.58,"duration":12.9},{"text":"Now, this comes out of Time Magazine dated May 14th, 1956.","start":422.58,"stop":428.19,"duration":5.61},{"text":"I have no reason to question the authority of the authoritativeness of this statement as a statistic.","start":428.19,"stop":435.708,"duration":7.52},{"text":"Now, in listening to the arguments that have gone long in this -- in -- in the Swanson case, I -- I observed, if I may say so state, a -- a confusion.","start":435.708,"stop":450.555,"duration":14.85},{"text":"The question in my humble judgment as to whether diversity exists or does not exist in any case, it has been clearly stated by Mr. Justice Frankfurter in the Indianapolis case.","start":450.555,"stop":463.786,"duration":13.23},{"text":"And we have gone -- we have actually, in our brief applied the reasoning of Mr. Justice Frankfurter in the Indianapolis case to the present case and we have said in point two, I quote from page 22 of my brief, The Warner directorate is a validly on the defendant side of the matter in controversy.","start":463.786,"stop":490.931,"duration":27.14},{"text":"It was error to realign the corporation as a -- as a complainant.","start":490.931,"stop":495.551,"duration":4.62},{"text":"And using Mr. Justice Frankfurter's words in the Indianapolis case, I said that only if the expensive judicial integrity, judicial integrity, in quotes, may Warner be alive with the complainant in this case in face of directors' admissions which I test to say the least that they are not on the complainant side of the dispute.","start":495.551,"stop":521.592,"duration":26.04},{"text":"In face of Warner counsels, that is the corporation counsels admission, that they are not antagonistic to the step.","start":521.592,"stop":529.072,"duration":7.48},{"text":"They are antagonistic to the suit but the corporation is at one with the defendants in a common contention, namely, the challenge dealings in which if the corporation and these directors against whom we allege this wrongdoing, again, in a common contention, namely, to challenge dealings which -- in which it and they participate are unlawful.","start":529.072,"stop":553.422,"duration":24.35}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Levy, may I interrupt you to just summarize the material on the basis of which the criteria in which you have invoked is to be determined.","start":553.422,"stop":563.47,"duration":10.05},{"text":"What are facts in short --","start":563.47,"stop":565.37,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"In this case?","start":565.37,"stop":565.4,"duration":0.03}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"In the three months -- yes, in this case, at least the generalities that one can agree with --","start":565.4,"stop":571.15,"duration":5.75}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Very well.","start":571.15,"stop":571.452,"duration":0.3}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- interpolate in the bite of it.","start":571.452,"stop":572.802,"duration":1.35}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Very well.","start":572.802,"stop":573.272,"duration":0.47},{"text":"I have --","start":573.272,"stop":573.282,"duration":0.01}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What are the facts in this case which are before us?","start":573.282,"stop":577.692,"duration":4.41},{"text":"I assume there's no such controversy in this case as in the prior one as to what facts are really before us so --","start":577.692,"stop":582.292,"duration":4.6}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think so.","start":582.292,"stop":583.222,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You don't think so.","start":583.222,"stop":583.862,"duration":0.64}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":583.862,"stop":583.962,"duration":0.1}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, then what are the facts --","start":583.962,"stop":586.132,"duration":2.17}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Very well.","start":586.132,"stop":586.162,"duration":0.03}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- which I take it your Brother will agree with or with the usual differences of counsel in stating the facts.","start":586.162,"stop":592.632,"duration":6.47}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"I have stated these facts, Your Honor, in my statement of the case beginning at page 4 and continuing on until page 12.","start":592.632,"stop":603.832,"duration":11.2},{"text":"Briefly --","start":603.832,"stop":605.212,"duration":1.38}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What are the sources?","start":605.212,"stop":606.062,"duration":0.85},{"text":"Its complaint is just state --","start":606.062,"stop":608.312,"duration":2.25}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":608.312,"stop":608.632,"duration":0.32}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- all the sources on which you -- from which the facts arrived on which we must act on this case.","start":608.632,"stop":614.955,"duration":6.32}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"In this case, we have both alleged and, of course, there was testimony in this case as Your Honors.","start":614.955,"stop":622.981,"duration":8.03},{"text":"I -- I don't think I have made that thing clear and if Your Honors haven't read my brief, maybe I should say this.","start":622.981,"stop":628.611,"duration":5.63}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I'm one of these judges who doesn't read the briefs as it does.","start":628.611,"stop":631.191,"duration":2.58}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then maybe -- maybe I should -- maybe I should --","start":631.191,"stop":633.554,"duration":2.36}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Who deal any such compulsion and I have good reason for not doing it myself whatever or anybody else's reason for himself.","start":633.554,"stop":640.104,"duration":6.55}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then may I -- may I state the facts briefly.","start":640.104,"stop":645.923,"duration":5.82},{"text":"Our client is a New York citizen and a stockholder of Warner Brothers Pictures.","start":645.923,"stop":650.914,"duration":4.99},{"text":"He commenced this action in the District Court in California back in 1948.","start":650.914,"stop":660.184,"duration":9.27},{"text":"He commenced it against his corporation, the Warner Corporation, Harry and Jack Warner, the president and vice-president of the company, Harry Warner's son-in-law, Milton Sperling, and another corporation, namely, United, which was owned by the son-in-law.","start":660.184,"stop":679.164,"duration":18.98},{"text":"Now, there would have been no question of diversity in this case who had it not been for the fact that Warner corporation, the stockholders company, is a Delaware corporation and the son-in-law's company happens to be a Delaware corporation.","start":679.164,"stop":693.094,"duration":13.93},{"text":"Now, having joined as defendants, the stockholders corporation, namely, Warner for short, and United, the son-in-law's corporation, if there -- if the corporation is realigned, that is the stockholders corporation is realigned on the side of the plaintiff, obviously, diversity is lost.","start":693.094,"stop":713.165,"duration":20.07},{"text":"Having done so, the defendants put in an answer.","start":713.165,"stop":717.916,"duration":4.75},{"text":"Now, the -- by the defendants, I mean the corporation, Warner, Harry and Jack Warner, they all appeared by the same attorneys and joined in a common answer in which they denied, (1), that the plaintiff was a citizen of New York, (2), they denied all of the allegations of alleged wrongdoing and breach of trust that the complainant had alleged in this complaint, namely, the making of a series of contracts and the dealings between the Warner corporation and the son-in-law's corporation which the gist of which was that there was over reaching and self-dealing, bringing about an unwarranted and unjust enrichment in favor of the son-in-law and to the detriment of the corporation.","start":717.916,"stop":769.567,"duration":51.65},{"text":"Now, of course, this unjust enrichment didn't stop merely with the making of a contract or with the signing of a contract or with the dealings of the parties over a number of years.","start":769.567,"stop":779.423,"duration":9.86},{"text":"And incidentally, while this action was pending, amendments were made to this -- this contract and this joint venture between the Warner corporation and the son-in-law's corporation was not only continued but was increased in scope from time to time, more and more pictures were added which the son-in-law's corporation was to produce and on which he was to get 50% of the profits.","start":779.423,"stop":804.243,"duration":24.82},{"text":"Now, the -- the basic claim of the stockholder here is that something was given away to the son-in-law by a doting father-in-law.","start":804.243,"stop":812.514,"duration":8.27},{"text":"Now, that's the summon substance of that.","start":812.514,"stop":815.966,"duration":3.45},{"text":"Having taken the position, when -- when I say having taken the position, I mean by the corporation that this was perfectly good and advantageous to the company, they were going to make a lot of money and this was -- this was good business to do it.","start":815.966,"stop":833.703,"duration":17.74},{"text":"The plaintiff went on to discovery and for a long period of time, there were -- there was a lot of discovery, admissions, request for admissions and depositions and interrogatories to this effect.","start":833.703,"stop":846.715,"duration":13.01},{"text":"Finally, we came down to pretrial.","start":846.715,"stop":853.134,"duration":6.42},{"text":"There was no suggestion in the answer or there was no suggestion up to this time.","start":853.134,"stop":857.094,"duration":3.96},{"text":"Now, this pretrial happens some two or three years after the action have been commenced or maybe four.","start":857.094,"stop":862.524,"duration":5.43},{"text":"There was no suggestion up to that time that there was a lack of diversity here.","start":862.524,"stop":867.284,"duration":4.76},{"text":"Judge Mathes at pretrial questioned counsel with respect to that and sua sponte raised the question which he was entitled to do and as the -- this Court has held that this Court can do it all when -- when it gets here.","start":867.284,"stop":883.27,"duration":15.99},{"text":"In other words, if there was no jurisdiction, there was no jurisdiction no matter how long the case had gone on and no matter when it was raised or no matter how somnolent and sleepy everybody was on the question up to that.","start":883.27,"stop":897.029,"duration":13.76},{"text":"Having raised that question as the findings show in this case, the judge made an order practically as follows and I -- I stated in my brief this way, the merits of the controversy, namely, whether the Warner-United dealings are in fact unlawful and should be terminated and whether United -- Warner-United contract should be ordered canceled to the extent that they remain unexecuted or not reach.","start":897.029,"stop":925.809,"duration":28.78},{"text":"The Court ordered two issues to be tried, namely, one, jurisdiction, and two, the statute of limitations.","start":925.809,"stop":932.409,"duration":6.6},{"text":"He said, he should be inquired into preliminarily before we go ahead.","start":932.409,"stop":936.38,"duration":3.97},{"text":"Let's see whether this Court has jurisdiction before we go on and rightfully so.","start":936.38,"stop":941.78,"duration":5.4},{"text":"The parties were directed to present evidence and I have this in quotes and emphasize only as to those issues and the findings go on to say, “Thereupon, evidence on behalf of plaintiff and defendants, it was offered and received and the cause argued and submitted on the two above stated issues only.”","start":941.78,"stop":962.873,"duration":21.09},{"text":"So then, it is clear from this finding that Judge Mathes was concerned primarily and only as it turned out to be with the question of diversity jurisdiction and even the question of the statute of limitations although considerable evidence was introduced on it.","start":962.873,"stop":979.263,"duration":16.39},{"text":"It was not reached.","start":979.263,"stop":980.933,"duration":1.67},{"text":"Judge Mathes held as follows and this is in concurred distinction to the holding in the Swanson case.","start":980.933,"stop":988.733,"duration":7.8},{"text":"And may I briefly summarize what I believe the holding in the Swanson case is before ours.","start":988.733,"stop":993.853,"duration":5.12},{"text":"The holding in the Swanson case is that in the absence of a showing, that the law -- that the directorate was hostile to the prosecution of the suit, the corporation should not be aligned as a defendant.","start":993.853,"stop":1006.765,"duration":12.91},{"text":"Now, that's the summon substance of the holding in the Swanson case.","start":1006.765,"stop":1010.475,"duration":3.71},{"text":"The holding in our case, however, in the -- in the Sperling case, it goes beyond that.","start":1010.475,"stop":1017.125,"duration":6.65},{"text":"The Court says, “That isn't enough.”","start":1017.125,"stop":1018.985,"duration":1.86},{"text":"The holding here is that neither a showing that the directorate is hostile to the prosecution of the suit nor a showing that the directorate is antagonistic to the objects of the suit is sufficient to warrant the corporation's alignment as a defendant.","start":1018.985,"stop":1036.525,"duration":17.54},{"text":"Nothing short of preponderating proof that the corporation was actually dominated and controlled by the co-defendants can save the corporation from being realigned as a plaintiff.","start":1036.525,"stop":1051.55,"duration":15.02},{"text":"Now, we say that that is not the law and has never been the law.","start":1051.55,"stop":1057.86,"duration":6.31},{"text":"Neither Doctor against Harrington has held that, nor has Venner against the Great Northern held that.","start":1057.86,"stop":1064.561,"duration":6.7},{"text":"And while I'm on that subject, may I -- may I say what --","start":1064.561,"stop":1070.655,"duration":6.09}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Let's see.","start":1070.655,"stop":1070.925,"duration":0.27},{"text":"Does that mean, do you read that as saying that it's not enough to show that however corrupt maybe the board of directors and however corrupt their motivation not to bring the action, the stockholder has actually to show that the corporation itself is a captive of the defendants not connected with the corporation?","start":1070.925,"stop":1091.045,"duration":20.12},{"text":"Do you go that far?","start":1091.045,"stop":1092.055,"duration":1.01}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor, I -- I -- no, I -- I think what Judge Mathes said virtually was this.","start":1092.055,"stop":1098.925,"duration":6.87},{"text":"He says, the stockholder is incumbent upon the stockholder and it's a prerequisite to -- as right to be heard in the federal court.","start":1098.925,"stop":1107.585,"duration":8.66},{"text":"It is incumbent upon a stockholder to show that the directorate that each and every member of that board of directors was actually dominated and controlled in this case by the president and vice-president that he controlled them.","start":1107.585,"stop":1122.78,"duration":15.19},{"text":"And that they were simply, as Mr. Justice Douglas in his article in the directors who do not direct practically, I think called them directorial gigolos or something to that effect.","start":1122.78,"stop":1138.095,"duration":15.32},{"text":"That's about the size of it.","start":1138.095,"stop":1139.305,"duration":1.21},{"text":"That is the holding of Judge Mathes.","start":1139.305,"stop":1142.075,"duration":2.77},{"text":"You have to go that far.","start":1142.075,"stop":1143.41,"duration":1.34},{"text":"And in my petition for certiorari, Your Honor, I have -- and I refer to page 13, I have made this remark with respect to that.","start":1143.41,"stop":1153.4,"duration":9.99},{"text":"Admissions like the foregoing and I -- in a moment state what these admissions were, admissions like the foregoing will fall short of proof by preponderance of the evidence that the directory was dominated and controlled by the alleged wrongdoers because as appellees successfully contended in the court below, men who posses personal strength and integrity cannot be controlled by such venal considerations or substantial annual salaries from the corporation.","start":1153.4,"stop":1184.531,"duration":31.13},{"text":"In short, the decision of the courts below in essence is -- or in essence required the stockholder to demonstrate to an almost mathematical certainty that the ethical current in each of his company's directors is not adequate to overcome, prompt this himself.","start":1184.531,"stop":1204.247,"duration":19.72},{"text":"And I went on to say a virtually impossible task and a task which with deference to the courts below seems decidedly out of harmony with this Court's recent observations, and I refer to Mr. Justice Reeds' observation in Koster against Lumbermens in which he said it has been the whole course of our law to break down the barriers against calling corporations to account in all States where they're maybe doing business and Mr. Justice Black's observation in that same case as follows, namely, the whole trend of recent congressional legislation has been to protect corporate stock and security holders.","start":1204.247,"stop":1239.752,"duration":35.5},{"text":"See for example, Securities Act of 1933.","start":1239.752,"stop":1242.822,"duration":3.07},{"text":"But this legislation was not intended as a complete substitute for the antidote by stockholder suits for the dangers inherent in the modern development of frequent conflicts between corporate owners and corporate managers.","start":1242.822,"stop":1257.677,"duration":14.86},{"text":"Now, the factual background upon which we make all of these statements, Your Honors, is briefly stated in our statement beginning on page 6 and going on for three or four pages.","start":1257.677,"stop":1281.65,"duration":23.97},{"text":"The inquiry that the Court had ordered into jurisdiction in this case unfolded, as we say the following realities, that one of us owned by the public.","start":1281.65,"stop":1291.911,"duration":10.26},{"text":"Its stock was distributed among some 30,000 stockholders.","start":1291.911,"stop":1296.451,"duration":4.54}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"We're turning on giving us all -- it came out on evidence after Judge Mathes put this question -- these issues, is that right?","start":1296.451,"stop":1301.701,"duration":5.25}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, Your Honor.","start":1301.701,"stop":1302.881,"duration":1.18},{"text":"These are the matters that came up in evidence before Judge Mathes and the reason why we stated or brought these things out in evidence because we were under this impression and I believe that we were right.","start":1302.881,"stop":1315.341,"duration":12.46},{"text":"We took, as our text say, this Court's decision in Pacific Railroad against Ketchum and in the removal cases in which Chief Justice Waite laid down the following as the rule to be observed.","start":1315.341,"stop":1329.223,"duration":13.88},{"text":"He said, namely, that the District Court will \"ascertain the real matter in dispute and arrange the parties on one side or the other of that dispute.”","start":1329.223,"stop":1342.103,"duration":12.88},{"text":"Now, so that the District Court will know what the real matter in dispute is, we, the complainant, offered the following evidence.","start":1342.103,"stop":1349.663,"duration":7.56},{"text":"We -- we showed that the Warner was owned by the public that 30,000 people owned this stock and they're located all over the world.","start":1349.663,"stop":1357.683,"duration":8.02},{"text":"That three of the stockholders, namely, Harry and Jack Warner and his brother Albert, between them have a working control of the company.","start":1357.683,"stop":1366.273,"duration":8.59},{"text":"They owned between 15% and 20% of the stock.","start":1366.273,"stop":1370.623,"duration":4.35},{"text":"We showed by -- and these are statements out of the mouths of the directors and they are stated on page 6 and 7 of our brief and we showed that the -- that Harry and Jack and Albert Warner run the company, run in quotations.","start":1370.623,"stop":1390.222,"duration":19.6},{"text":"They --","start":1390.222,"stop":1390.992,"duration":0.77}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Levy, may I ask, is the object of this argument to show that the findings made by Judge Mathes to the -- are not supported by evidence?","start":1390.992,"stop":1400.943,"duration":9.95}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor, no.","start":1400.943,"stop":1402.687,"duration":1.74},{"text":"Only incidentally am I -- am I relating these things in answer to Mr. Justice Frankfurter as to what the factual background is that came out before of Mr. Justice Mathes.","start":1402.687,"stop":1412.007,"duration":9.32}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"You did have an 18-day trial up before Judge Mathes.","start":1412.007,"stop":1414.687,"duration":2.68}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"There was a lot -- when we say -- we didn't have an 18-day trial in the first place, Your Honor.","start":1414.687,"stop":1419.602,"duration":4.92},{"text":"I don't think it went on that long and on the second place --","start":1419.602,"stop":1422.552,"duration":2.95}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"If he --","start":1422.552,"stop":1423.462,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, some 15 days but we had short sessions as well as long sessions and -- and in during that time, what we have was this, Your Honor, we could have all -- practically all of what, let's say most of what went into evidence in this record, could have been just -- I could have just said I -- I offer an evidence of these interrogatories or I offer an evidence of these requests for admissions.","start":1423.462,"stop":1446.558,"duration":23.1},{"text":"Now, they were this thick instead of that, we read them.","start":1446.558,"stop":1450.438,"duration":3.88}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, isn't the trouble --","start":1450.438,"stop":1450.868,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"So that --","start":1450.868,"stop":1451.398,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Levy, however, if Judge Mathes' findings made it to conclusion of the trial are supported by -- by evidence, then we're now down to questions of law, aren't we?","start":1451.398,"stop":1462.258,"duration":10.86}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":1462.258,"stop":1463.598,"duration":1.34},{"text":"In other words, I am assuming for the sake of the argument and is my question -- as my question was paused in this case.","start":1463.598,"stop":1470.531,"duration":6.93},{"text":"I am assuming for the sake of this argument that these directors were not controlled.","start":1470.531,"stop":1476.047,"duration":5.52}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, we're not?","start":1476.047,"stop":1477.357,"duration":1.31}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"We're not controlled, yes, Your Honor.","start":1477.357,"stop":1479.507,"duration":2.15}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Which directors?","start":1479.507,"stop":1480.557,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"The Warner directors --","start":1480.557,"stop":1481.847,"duration":1.29}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"As I --","start":1481.847,"stop":1481.987,"duration":0.14}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"-- all of them.","start":1481.987,"stop":1482.476,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- as I understood your argument, I may have hoped they must concede it, you persuaded me if what you said was so that the Warner Brothers with a 15% to 20% working interest controlled in the sense determined what that corporation would or wouldn't do.","start":1482.476,"stop":1501.515,"duration":19.04}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":1501.515,"stop":1502.155,"duration":0.64}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) --","start":1502.155,"stop":1502.205,"duration":0.05}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what the record shows.","start":1502.205,"stop":1504.605,"duration":2.4}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You said that's what the record shows that having that control determining what the corporation which they control can -- would or would not do by their ipse dixit that in fact these stockholders said, “You are milking the corporation in what I have a monetary interest by giving favors by trigging the outside and the way in which you shouldn't be treated if you merely regard the corporate interest.","start":1504.605,"stop":1534.557,"duration":29.95}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":1534.557,"stop":1534.737,"duration":0.18}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Isn't that what you said?","start":1534.737,"stop":1535.637,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":1535.637,"stop":1536.207,"duration":0.57}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, that being so, your argument I think it is that Judge Mathes applied the wrong legal doctrine as Justice Whittaker suggests, applied the wrong legal standard for determining when you transfer a nominal plaintiff over to the defendant's side.","start":1536.207,"stop":1554.292,"duration":18.08},{"text":"Isn't that your position?","start":1554.292,"stop":1556.372,"duration":2.08}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"He applied the wrong legal standards.","start":1556.372,"stop":1559.432,"duration":3.06},{"text":"Now, I'm going beyond that, Your Honor.","start":1559.432,"stop":1561.067,"duration":1.63},{"text":"I say that assuming for the sake of the argument, he was -- that his findings were correct.","start":1561.067,"stop":1566.467,"duration":5.4}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1566.467,"stop":1566.807,"duration":0.34}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Namely, he found that these were -- this in -- that Warner -- that Harry and Jack Warner despite the fact that the directors had testified that if they became persona non grata to Harry and Jack Warner, they'd be through and so they did and that -- those are admissions in the record.","start":1566.807,"stop":1581.911,"duration":15.1}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, does that mean that -- that what you said that this 15%-20% Warners did not have control?","start":1581.911,"stop":1588.731,"duration":6.82}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, it means they -- they had control.","start":1588.731,"stop":1590.991,"duration":2.26},{"text":"But I'm assuming --","start":1590.991,"stop":1591.081,"duration":0.09}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if they had control, then judge -- then -- then, how can the fellows saying that the fellow has control hasn't got control?","start":1591.081,"stop":1597.621,"duration":6.54},{"text":"I don't understand that.","start":1597.621,"stop":1598.371,"duration":0.75}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's what Judge Mathes said.","start":1598.371,"stop":1600.821,"duration":2.45},{"text":"He said he had -- they said that these men did -- these men were disinterested men.","start":1600.821,"stop":1606.186,"duration":5.37}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"You said they acted in good faith and this was a matter of judgment.","start":1606.186,"stop":1609.446,"duration":3.26}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then he must have --","start":1609.446,"stop":1609.686,"duration":0.24}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"He said -- he said that --","start":1609.686,"stop":1610.616,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Then he must have rejected the conclusion which you and I under your inference have drawn from this testimony and hear the witnesses, then you're up against --","start":1610.616,"stop":1621.72,"duration":11.1}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"He didn't --","start":1621.72,"stop":1622.17,"duration":0.45}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- Justice Whittaker's question.","start":1622.17,"stop":1623.461,"duration":1.29}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"May I -- may I point this out, Your Honor.","start":1623.461,"stop":1627.321,"duration":3.86},{"text":"The witnesses that Your Honor speaks of were several directors, only one of which who appeared before Judge Mathes, the others, Judge Mathes never had the benefit of seeing these people anymore than Your Honors have (Voice Overlap) --","start":1627.321,"stop":1642.867,"duration":15.55}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then what's challenging as Justice Whittaker suggested to you a minute ago, you say that the conclusion which he arrived at is unfounded in law because it's unfounded in fact.","start":1642.867,"stop":1652.847,"duration":9.98}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"I say it's unfounded in law because it's unfounded in fact but I go on to say further that assuming that it is unfounded in law as well as unfounded in fact and assuming, however, that he have the right to make such findings.","start":1652.847,"stop":1667.91,"duration":15.06},{"text":"I say, nevertheless, I come to this point assuming in other words that these directors were all honest men.","start":1667.91,"stop":1675.835,"duration":7.92}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And capable of exercising --","start":1675.835,"stop":1677.365,"duration":1.53}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Capable --","start":1677.365,"stop":1677.525,"duration":0.16}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- their honesty.","start":1677.525,"stop":1678.585,"duration":1.06}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"-- capable of exercising their -- their good business judgment.","start":1678.585,"stop":1683.175,"duration":4.59}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And in fact exercising (Voice Overlap) --","start":1683.175,"stop":1684.662,"duration":1.49}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"And in fact exercise and I will go that far and say in fact exercise.","start":1684.662,"stop":1690.632,"duration":5.97},{"text":"I say this that where a stockholder comes in and says, \"You milked this corporation for the benefit of this boy.\"","start":1690.632,"stop":1700.532,"duration":9.9},{"text":"The fact that every one of these men is honest and has exercised to the best of his ability, this interested of an independent judgment, nevertheless, does not argue for the fact that these men cannot be wrong.","start":1700.532,"stop":1714.286,"duration":13.75},{"text":"I say that the road to a fraud maybe bottomed down the best of intentions.","start":1714.286,"stop":1719.086,"duration":4.8}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But they (Voice Overlap) --","start":1719.086,"stop":1719.346,"duration":0.26}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, let us assume --","start":1719.346,"stop":1720.686,"duration":1.34}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But you -- you just negative our right to conclude that Judge Mathes was wrong or unjustified on the record in finding there was no fraud.","start":1720.686,"stop":1733.576,"duration":12.89},{"text":"If there was fraud, then we got no problem.","start":1733.576,"stop":1735.966,"duration":2.39}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"May it please, Your Honor, Mr. Judge Mathes did not find that there was no fraud.","start":1735.966,"stop":1740.416,"duration":4.45},{"text":"What he found was this.","start":1740.416,"stop":1742.76,"duration":2.34},{"text":"He found that these men, when they approve this arrangement, were not acting in bad faith.","start":1742.76,"stop":1749.54,"duration":6.78},{"text":"They intended this to be good.","start":1749.54,"stop":1752.83,"duration":3.29},{"text":"They considered this to be good.","start":1752.83,"stop":1755.48,"duration":2.65},{"text":"The proposed findings and I call Your Honors attention to the record on this point, the proposed findings on page 74 of the record, Your Honors will notice -- Your Honors will notice (Voice Overlap).","start":1755.48,"stop":1782.261,"duration":26.78}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What do you mean by proposed findings?","start":1782.261,"stop":1784.301,"duration":2.04}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"These are the findings that the successful party proposed to Judge Mathes.","start":1784.301,"stop":1789.921,"duration":5.62}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And he made them as amended?","start":1789.921,"stop":1791.821,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"And he deleted certain -- he deleted certain portions of the record and --","start":1791.821,"stop":1796.761,"duration":4.94}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But this isn't what he actually found.","start":1796.761,"stop":1798.341,"duration":1.58}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":1798.341,"stop":1799.081,"duration":0.74}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"All right.","start":1799.081,"stop":1799.231,"duration":0.15}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, these deletions of the things that I particularly call Your Honors attention to, Your Honor said something a moment ago create -- made -- made a premise, namely, that Judge Mathes had found that no fraud had been committed here.","start":1799.231,"stop":1812.38,"duration":13.15},{"text":"I say that is not the fact and Judge Mathes did not find it to be the fact.","start":1812.38,"stop":1816.88,"duration":4.5},{"text":"Here is what he said, let us take first what the proposal is that Judge Mathes find.","start":1816.88,"stop":1823.151,"duration":6.27},{"text":"Our opponents asked the Court to find that the board of directors of Warner Brothers is composed of 11 men of whom the defendants Harry --","start":1823.151,"stop":1829.886,"duration":6.73}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is that, Mr. --","start":1829.886,"stop":1830.746,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"On page 74, Your Honor, of Volume 1.","start":1830.746,"stop":1833.736,"duration":2.99}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Bottom of the page -- bottom words.","start":1833.736,"stop":1837.136,"duration":3.4}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"But three, that the contract in controversy was and all amendments and supplements thereto were and are sound business arrangements made and entered in good faith and without fraud.","start":1837.136,"stop":1852.232,"duration":15.1},{"text":"Now, what Judge Mathes did was struck out, the ultimate fact.","start":1852.232,"stop":1856.962,"duration":4.73},{"text":"He did not find that these contracts were honest and without fraud.","start":1856.962,"stop":1864.546,"duration":7.58},{"text":"He said they were intended to be.","start":1864.546,"stop":1870.448,"duration":5.9},{"text":"They were intended by the directors to be a -- a benefit to the company and the directors considered them.","start":1870.448,"stop":1879.568,"duration":9.12}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, he -- he's very categorical in saying -- in signing his name to a finding that the contract in question, in controversy was made and entered into in good faith and without fraud.","start":1879.568,"stop":1892.488,"duration":12.92}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":1892.488,"stop":1893.798,"duration":1.31},{"text":"He says under the -- under the record (Voice Overlap) --","start":1893.798,"stop":1894.178,"duration":0.38}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"There weren't -- on the finding, there was no fraud.","start":1894.178,"stop":1896.728,"duration":2.55}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, because he -- what he says there, Your Honor, he didn't say, \"I examined this whole situation and I find that this son-in-law wasn't -- wasn't treated -- wasn't treated with -- with favor.”","start":1896.728,"stop":1907.528,"duration":10.8},{"text":"He says this, “The directors examined this thing and they came to the conclusion in their opinion that this was all right.”","start":1907.528,"stop":1915.885,"duration":8.36},{"text":"But I don't say it's all right.","start":1915.885,"stop":1917.115,"duration":1.23}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Because -- between what says.","start":1917.115,"stop":1917.535,"duration":0.42}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"He could be --","start":1917.535,"stop":1918.705,"duration":1.17}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But why do you paraphrase?","start":1918.705,"stop":1920.535,"duration":1.83},{"text":"He says, the contract in controversy was made and entered into in good faith and without fraud.","start":1920.535,"stop":1927.021,"duration":6.49}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":1927.021,"stop":1928.401,"duration":1.38},{"text":"That isn't the finding in my humble judgment that that contract is not fraudulent.","start":1928.401,"stop":1933.584,"duration":5.18}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"What does it mean then?","start":1933.584,"stop":1934.524,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it means this, Your Honor.","start":1934.524,"stop":1936.404,"duration":1.88},{"text":"It means that these directors when this contract was placed before them and they said, “Very well, we'll pass on this.”","start":1936.404,"stop":1945.128,"duration":8.72},{"text":"And at the time they did, they didn't intend to hurt the company.","start":1945.128,"stop":1950.348,"duration":5.22},{"text":"They weren't out to hurt the company.","start":1950.348,"stop":1953.228,"duration":2.88},{"text":"That's all but it is a far cry from the director saying -- from saying that the directors were honest men and they didn't intend to hurt the company to saying that what actually was contained in that contract and the dealings under that contract between these two corporations were not, as a matter of fact, unwarrantedly favorable to a son-in-law and did not, in fact, militate in the direction of siphoning a -- a part of Warner's capital into the coffers of a -- of a favorite boy.","start":1953.228,"stop":1988.614,"duration":35.39},{"text":"It's quite a different thing and the fact that Judge Mathes was careful enough to X this out is another indication of the fact.","start":1988.614,"stop":1998.344,"duration":9.73},{"text":"And furthermore may I say this, Your Honor, another evidence of the fact that Judge Mathes didn't find that there was actual fraud here in the sense these -- whether these dealings were actually closure or not, let me put it that way, is this.","start":1998.344,"stop":2015.719,"duration":17.38},{"text":"Had he done so, he would have assumed jurisdiction.","start":2015.719,"stop":2018.449,"duration":2.73},{"text":"He says, he never assumed jurisdiction in this case.","start":2018.449,"stop":2022.205,"duration":3.76},{"text":"He says he never tried the merits in this case.","start":2022.205,"stop":2024.615,"duration":2.41},{"text":"He ordered the parties not to present evidence on the merits in this case.","start":2024.615,"stop":2028.715,"duration":4.1},{"text":"He confined and limited the issue, the hearing to questions involving whether -- involving what whether or not there was diversity in this case.","start":2028.715,"stop":2039.621,"duration":10.91}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"It's --","start":2039.621,"stop":2039.901,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"What -- pardon me?","start":2039.901,"stop":2041.151,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"It's just a fact raised for the pleading preliminary to the determination of the question of whether he had time to try the case.","start":2041.151,"stop":2048.471,"duration":7.32}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":2048.471,"stop":2049.221,"duration":0.75},{"text":"The question before Judge Mathes was simply this, Have I or have I not the power to examine into the merits of this thing and determine whether this was an honest deal or was not an honest deal.","start":2049.221,"stop":2060.024,"duration":10.8},{"text":"First of all, I'm going to determine whether I have the power as the federal court does.","start":2060.024,"stop":2064.554,"duration":4.53},{"text":"Now, what he meant, he makes these findings and he says this, before I can have the power to decide this case, the stockholder must show me not only that the directors are hostile to him, not only that they are antagonistic to him in anyway, unless he shows and by preponderating evidence that each and everyone of these men were -- was dominated and controlled by the three Warner Brothers so that they were not free agents.","start":2064.554,"stop":2106.225,"duration":41.67},{"text":"I cannot decide this case because then the corporation must be aligned on the other side of the fence and notwithstanding the fact -- notwithstanding the fact that the corporation has taken the position and concedes it contrary to the stockholders notwithstanding any of such things all together.","start":2106.225,"stop":2126.577,"duration":20.35},{"text":"Now, we say that that is not the law in this case, neither Doctor against Harrington has held that, neither Venner against the Great Northern hasn't held that.","start":2126.577,"stop":2134.213,"duration":7.64}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, in the light of these findings which you said you're willing to accept for the purposes of your argument, as I understand it you believe it.","start":2134.213,"stop":2139.408,"duration":5.19}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2139.408,"stop":2140.478,"duration":1.07}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Will you phrase what you think the rule is in the light of these findings?","start":2140.478,"stop":2146.251,"duration":5.77}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"The rule of alignment?","start":2146.251,"stop":2147.431,"duration":1.18}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, in light of these findings?","start":2147.431,"stop":2152.361,"duration":4.93}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That where a stockholder can show or show us whether it is pleadings or by affidavit or by evidence taken orally that the corporation, his corporation, the stockholder's corporation is hostile, is inimical to the objects of the suit under those conditions, the corporation has to be aligned as a defendant where he cannot show that the corporation is hostile, not --","start":2152.361,"stop":2188.171,"duration":35.81}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) --","start":2188.171,"stop":2188.411,"duration":0.24}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"-- to the best interest of the corporation as -- as Judge Mathes held.","start":2188.411,"stop":2192.721,"duration":4.31},{"text":"What Judge Mathes held here is this, it isn't enough for the stockholder to show that the corporation was hostile to him or that the directors were hostile.","start":2192.721,"stop":2202.881,"duration":10.16},{"text":"He must show that they were hostile not to him or to the commencement of the action or to its object.","start":2202.881,"stop":2210.292,"duration":7.41},{"text":"He must show that they are hostile to the best interest of the corporation.","start":2210.292,"stop":2214.502,"duration":4.21},{"text":"Now --","start":2214.502,"stop":2214.522,"duration":0.02}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Isn't that the law?","start":2214.522,"stop":2215.432,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"-- I contend this, Your Honor","start":2215.432,"stop":2217.152,"duration":1.72},{"text":"If that's the situation, how can he do that unless he tries the merits as the Chief Justice suggested to one of the gentlemen who argued the case before this?","start":2217.152,"stop":2228.52,"duration":11.37},{"text":"How can he do this unless he tries all the merits?","start":2228.52,"stop":2231.66,"duration":3.14},{"text":"Now, if that were the rule, what will happen?","start":2231.66,"stop":2234.94,"duration":3.28},{"text":"Judge Mathes would have gone along and tried the merits of the controversy.","start":2234.94,"stop":2239.134,"duration":4.19},{"text":"(Voice Overlap) --","start":2239.134,"stop":2239.174,"duration":0.04}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Mr. Levy, you -- you said at the very outset of your argument that you did not agree with Mr. Doyle's answer to me in the previous case.","start":2239.174,"stop":2246.109,"duration":6.93}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":2246.109,"stop":2246.589,"duration":0.48}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And it seems to me that the findings of the fact made here by Judge Mathes are the very findings which I hypothesized from Mr. Doyle when I put in the question to him, namely, when acting in good faith and in the exercise of an independent business judgment, they resolve not to bring the suit.","start":2246.589,"stop":2267.399,"duration":20.81},{"text":"Mr. Doyle's proposition was that never let -- in that circumstance, the corporation was to be aligned on the side of the defendant as I understood it.","start":2267.399,"stop":2278.129,"duration":10.73}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, except --","start":2278.129,"stop":2278.639,"duration":0.51}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"And you said you disagreed with that.","start":2278.639,"stop":2280.469,"duration":1.83}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I disagreed with it for this reason.","start":2280.469,"stop":2282.432,"duration":1.96},{"text":"I didn't -- it - it struck me that a mere disagreement between a stockholder and the directors of a corporation that has no real basis are just -- a disagreement with stockholders as I think you ought to bring this thing and the -- and the directors say, \"We don't think you all agreed.","start":2282.432,"stop":2300.672,"duration":18.24},{"text":"You haven't showed us why.\"","start":2300.672,"stop":2303.192,"duration":2.52},{"text":"There's no reason for it at all and the stockholders simply remained quiet about it and it's just -- just arbitrary and capricious about it.","start":2303.192,"stop":2312.402,"duration":9.21},{"text":"That's no reason.","start":2312.402,"stop":2313.252,"duration":0.85},{"text":"I mean I don't think that that would establish diversity because he hasn't shown that the corporation is antagonistic, is hostile to what he claim is right, unless the -- when the stockholder comes into Court and he says, \"Look, here is a series of acts that were done.","start":2313.252,"stop":2332.065,"duration":18.81},{"text":"These things I say are wrong.","start":2332.065,"stop":2334.355,"duration":2.29},{"text":"They are evil.\"","start":2334.355,"stop":2336.155,"duration":1.8},{"text":"The corporate director say, \"Oh, no, we regard these things as good and rightful.\"","start":2336.155,"stop":2342.125,"duration":5.97},{"text":"You have what Mr. Justice Frankfurter pointed out to be inevitable.","start":2342.125,"stop":2346.445,"duration":4.32},{"text":"You have a situation where one side says, “Yes” and the other side says, “No.”","start":2346.445,"stop":2351.459,"duration":5.01},{"text":"In this case, we have this situation.","start":2351.459,"stop":2354.069,"duration":2.61},{"text":"Here is the Warner outfit, the corporation, being aligned with the complainant against the directors of the company, the -- the president and vice-president when the corporation has no dispute at all with them.","start":2354.069,"stop":2368.149,"duration":14.08},{"text":"Now, as a matter if we go one step further and as I say in my second point adopting to Mr. Justice Frankfurter's language to this situation, we point out that only at the expense we say of judicial integrity can this be done in this case for these reasons.","start":2368.149,"stop":2391.629,"duration":23.48},{"text":"I put it this way.","start":2391.629,"stop":2392.549,"duration":0.92},{"text":"The error of both courts in realigning Warner Corporation as a complainant, thus destroying diversity becomes clear.","start":2392.549,"stop":2400.069,"duration":7.52},{"text":"When this Court's language in Indianapolis has adopted to the realities and that's the thing that we talked about in -- that Mr. Justice Frankfurter talked about in Indianapolis, the realities of the present case and it is seemed that the question which permeates this litigation is, \"Should the Court terminate and cancel the Warner-United arrangement as unlawful and unfair to Warner and compel the defendants -- the co-defendants to account for the injuries they -- they were alleged to?”","start":2400.069,"stop":2428.929,"duration":28.86},{"text":"Of course, we asked and our answer that the Court halt this --","start":2428.929,"stop":2432.094,"duration":3.16}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Levy --","start":2432.094,"stop":2432.774,"duration":0.68}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":2432.774,"stop":2432.864,"duration":0.09}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- do you conceived of a corporation as having an external existence apart from those who control its fate?","start":2432.864,"stop":2440.414,"duration":7.55}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what the Court in Doctor against Harrington said.","start":2440.414,"stop":2444.009,"duration":3.59}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That's because -- that's -- Doctor and Harrington was the case where the Harrington has a corporation by the throat.","start":2444.009,"stop":2453.799,"duration":9.79},{"text":"They were the corporation for purpose of that transaction.","start":2453.799,"stop":2457.859,"duration":4.06}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what you say has happened here?","start":2457.859,"stop":2460.73,"duration":2.87}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2460.73,"stop":2461.47,"duration":0.74},{"text":"I say that it happened here even though Mr. -- even though Judge Mathes found that in his opinion.","start":2461.47,"stop":2469.398,"duration":7.93}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That -- that may have happened here, but then you have to say that the findings of Judge Mathes to the contrary or to the outset, although he found that as a fact, he drew the wrong inference from it.","start":2469.398,"stop":2483.048,"duration":13.65}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":2483.048,"stop":2484.088,"duration":1.04}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Which is it?","start":2484.088,"stop":2485.338,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Both I think, Your Honor.","start":2485.338,"stop":2487.488,"duration":2.15},{"text":"And in the next place, I go one step further and I say, he assumed (Voice Overlap) --","start":2487.488,"stop":2489.998,"duration":2.51}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"When you go that part to that point, you don't have to go any further.","start":2489.998,"stop":2494.361,"duration":4.36}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then maybe I misunderstood Your Honor's question.","start":2494.361,"stop":2496.251,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I want to know this.","start":2496.251,"stop":2497.861,"duration":1.61}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2497.861,"stop":2498.291,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you say that Judge Mathes -- does it appear from the finding, the first one, does it appear from the finding that the people who control the fate of Warner Brothers as a corporation exercise an honest, non-fraudulent judgment?","start":2498.291,"stop":2515.275,"duration":16.98},{"text":"Is that a finding of it?","start":2515.275,"stop":2516.945,"duration":1.67},{"text":"If you challenge that as a finding, then -- then my next question isn't going to be what it is.","start":2516.945,"stop":2521.467,"duration":4.52},{"text":"But if you say that's what he found and that's as I read it, then the next question is, is that a baseless finding?","start":2521.467,"stop":2528.057,"duration":6.59},{"text":"Is there no evidence in this record which justify it?","start":2528.057,"stop":2530.577,"duration":2.52}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"There is not.","start":2530.577,"stop":2531.717,"duration":1.14}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Very well, I can understand that and -- or you can say, “Yes, he found that but he applied the wrong rule of law.","start":2531.717,"stop":2541.097,"duration":9.38}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"He found that when he applied the wrong rule of law.","start":2541.097,"stop":2543.367,"duration":2.27}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Because I thought your point was that the 20% interest that the Warner -- Warners had in the company is sufficient to make all the directors their nominees and pay.","start":2543.367,"stop":2554.098,"duration":10.73}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2554.098,"stop":2554.648,"duration":0.55}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that your point?","start":2554.648,"stop":2556.008,"duration":1.36}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2556.008,"stop":2556.328,"duration":0.32},{"text":"He says --","start":2556.328,"stop":2556.558,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And did he find that?","start":2556.558,"stop":2558.048,"duration":1.49}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"He didn't find it.","start":2558.048,"stop":2558.578,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"He -- he excluded it from his findings.","start":2558.578,"stop":2561.158,"duration":2.58}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What do you mean he excluded it?","start":2561.158,"stop":2562.038,"duration":0.88},{"text":"Did you mean he found the opposite?","start":2562.038,"stop":2563.465,"duration":1.43}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, he didn't find one or another, Your Honor.","start":2563.465,"stop":2564.325,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) irrelevant?","start":2564.325,"stop":2565.855,"duration":1.53},{"text":"Did he say it was irrelevant?","start":2565.855,"stop":2567.625,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, he said nothing of the kind.","start":2567.625,"stop":2569.095,"duration":1.47},{"text":"He simply confined these findings to one thing.","start":2569.095,"stop":2571.845,"duration":2.75},{"text":"It was because he was under this impression that before a corporation can be realigned as a complainant in a stockholder suit, the stockholder must show that the -- the directors were dominated in control and --","start":2571.845,"stop":2585.849,"duration":14}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But, Mr. Levy, what do you mean he didn't find out?","start":2585.849,"stop":2588.279,"duration":2.43},{"text":"What -- what am I reading at 75?","start":2588.279,"stop":2589.899,"duration":1.62},{"text":"And that even the corporation nor the directors or officers were shown that they at that time or at anytime under the domination or control of the three brothers, Warner above name, what do you mean he didn't find it?","start":2589.899,"stop":2600.437,"duration":10.54}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"He found that they were not under the domination and control of the three brothers.","start":2600.437,"stop":2604.167,"duration":3.73},{"text":"Oh, yes, he found that.","start":2604.167,"stop":2606.617,"duration":2.45}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then --","start":2606.617,"stop":2606.967,"duration":0.35}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) --","start":2606.967,"stop":2606.987,"duration":0.02}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- we can't find unless we find that that finding is based that they were under control and that's Doctor and Harrington.","start":2606.987,"stop":2614.317,"duration":7.33}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":2614.317,"stop":2614.937,"duration":0.62},{"text":"Doctor and Harrington -- may I say this, Doctor and Harrington was not decided on that issue at all.","start":2614.937,"stop":2620.617,"duration":5.68}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Doctor and Harrington were decided on a simple plain stock issue that the dominant control of that corporation did something in their self-interest and thereby deprived the Doctors of their right --","start":2620.617,"stop":2633.282,"duration":12.66}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"May I --","start":2633.282,"stop":2633.932,"duration":0.65}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- Doctor and Harrington case.","start":2633.932,"stop":2635.322,"duration":1.39}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"May I -- may I respectfully call Your Honors attention to --","start":2635.322,"stop":2642.612,"duration":7.29}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"One of the charge of Doctor and Harrington among others is the -- the brief opinion, so we can read it very quickly.","start":2642.612,"stop":2647.472,"duration":4.86}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2647.472,"stop":2648.462,"duration":0.99},{"text":"And may I point out that if Doctor, and -- and I say this advice, that after reading a lot of law on this thing, Your Honor, I believe that in the Doctor and Harrington case, I'll go so far as to say this, if there had been no allegation in the complaint in the Doctor and Harrington case of domination and control by the defendants, by the co-defendants of -- of the corporation under the stockholder, that complaint would -- the diversity would still be present in Doctor --","start":2648.462,"stop":2679.353,"duration":30.89}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Maybe it would --","start":2679.353,"stop":2679.913,"duration":0.56}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"-- against Harrington.","start":2679.913,"stop":2680.233,"duration":0.32}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- but the whole point of Doctor and Harrington was that a certificate came up here from Judge Lacombe of the Circuit Court in the Southern District asking this specific question and not aligning it and this Court said that -- and aligning it with the plaintiff, this Court said, “No”, because the people who actually has the corporation there by the throat were the fellows against whom you complained.","start":2680.233,"stop":2705.671,"duration":25.44}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"May I call Your Honors attention to this though.","start":2705.671,"stop":2709.701,"duration":4.03},{"text":"Here is what -- here is -- here's the language of the Court on this thing, it says the 94th rule in equity contemplates that there may be and provides for a suit by a stockholder in a corporation founded on rights which maybe properly asserted by the corporation.","start":2709.701,"stop":2727.583,"duration":17.88},{"text":"And the decisions of this Court established that such a suit when between citizens of different states involves a controversy cognizable in a -- in a court of the United States.","start":2727.583,"stop":2739.862,"duration":12.28},{"text":"The ultimate interest of a corporation maybe -- may defendant maybe the same as that may plaintiff -- plaintiff of the corporation maybe under a control antagonistic to him on how the -- what is the semantic meaning of the word antagonistic doesn't mean antagonistic of the corporation ultimate interest which require a trial of the merits in order to determine.","start":2739.862,"stop":2763.667,"duration":23.8},{"text":"And after you get a trial of the merits, what happens?","start":2763.667,"stop":2766.284,"duration":2.62},{"text":"The judge says, \"I have found that the plaintiff hasn't got a case but I cannot decide it because I have no jurisdiction.\"","start":2766.284,"stop":2772.984,"duration":6.7},{"text":"That's what it will amount to.","start":2772.984,"stop":2774.869,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Levy, you -- you've been interrupted so much.","start":2774.869,"stop":2779.079,"duration":4.21},{"text":"If you wish the rest of the time until adjournment, you may have it to --","start":2779.079,"stop":2783.424,"duration":4.34}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"May I say that --","start":2783.424,"stop":2784.094,"duration":0.67}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- to sum up.","start":2784.094,"stop":2785.514,"duration":1.42},{"text":"You may and counsel -- counsel may have an additional amount of time in responding.","start":2785.514,"stop":2791.214,"duration":5.7}]},{"speakerName":"Herman H. Levy","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you, Your Honor.","start":2791.214,"stop":2791.924,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"We'll go right ahead.","start":2791.924,"stop":2792.584,"duration":0.66}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) --","start":2792.584,"stop":2794.054,"duration":1.47}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I beg your pardon?","start":2794.054,"stop":2794.864,"duration":0.81}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Will I start now, Your Honor?","start":2794.864,"stop":2795.784,"duration":0.92}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, if you please.","start":2795.784,"stop":2798.524,"duration":2.74}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and Members of the Court.","start":2798.524,"stop":2804.598,"duration":6.07},{"text":"It has been well pointed out by Judge -- more and more of the justices that they should first find out what the facts are in determining that framework, what rule of law is after.","start":2804.598,"stop":2824.362,"duration":19.76},{"text":"We suggest most definitely that the facts are those which are found by Judge Mathes after a full scale trial lasting 15 days, consuming 2000 pages of transcript and many hundreds of dozens of exhibits.","start":2824.362,"stop":2848.537,"duration":24.17},{"text":"On the single question or the double question of the jurisdiction of the United States District Courts to entertain the action and the questions of whether the statute of limitations was a bar to the taking of the action and the fact that those two issues were coupled is logical because the issue of realignment and diversity jurisdictions depended on the question of whether the corporation was in hands hostile to its interest or whether it was dominated by the wrongdoers or otherwise unable to protect itself.","start":2848.537,"stop":2891.411,"duration":42.87},{"text":"And also basically, the question of statute of limitations depended upon a finding of fact covering the same subject matter because if the corporation had been unable to protect its own interests, the statute of limitations would not have been running against the action, whereas if it were able to protect his own interest, it would have been.","start":2891.411,"stop":2912.109,"duration":20.7},{"text":"However, in view of Judge Mathes' decision with reference to the -- to the basic question of diversity of jurisdiction, he never came to the point and obviously, he could not come to the point of deciding the -- the second question of statute of limitations because he had no jurisdiction to decide anything except that he had no jurisdiction.","start":2912.109,"stop":2935.707,"duration":23.6},{"text":"I may say, if the Court please, that frankly we were a little disappointed at the judges decision realizing the sincerity of his approach and the meticulous regard which Judge Mathes had for the limits of federal jurisdiction, a -- a regard which is probably unusual and probably accounts for the fact that there hasn't been, so far as I know, another case just like this where so much evidence has been taken where the real issues have really been decided because I suspect in many cases where judges who had less regard for the limits of federal jurisdiction, they may have gone ahead and decided the cases on the merits in favor of the defendants, they never came up on this point.","start":2935.707,"stop":2991.695,"duration":55.99},{"text":"But Judge Mathes did have that regard and as you're -- this Court will find when the examination of his very scholarly opinion, he -- he had a great deal of thought and -- and sincere work to the solution of the problem.","start":2991.695,"stop":3007.225,"duration":15.53},{"text":"However, with all this background of evidence, he made findings of facts which appears to me it would be utterly decisive of this case in view of our understanding of the meaning and effect of Doctor against Harrington and Venner against Great Northern and -- and Koster against Lumbermens Mutual and so forth.","start":3007.225,"stop":3032.554,"duration":25.33},{"text":"He found this, and I think it's worth reading these findings in full because they're not too long and yet, they are the very crux of this case, that the Board of Directors of Warner Brothers Pictures, Inc. is composed of 11 men of whom the defendants, Harry M. Warner and Jack L.Warner and their brother Albert Warner, not a defendant, but three, that the contract in controversy was made and entered into in good faith and without fraud.","start":3032.554,"stop":3061.794,"duration":29.24},{"text":"And said contract was intended by the directors to be of financial benefit to Warner Brothers Pictures, Inc. and its stockholders.","start":3061.794,"stop":3071.189,"duration":9.39},{"text":"And said contract was considered by said 11 members of the Board of Directors of Warner Brothers Pictures, Inc. to be a sound business arrangement for the best interest and future interests of the -- for the best present and future interests of the corporation.","start":3071.189,"stop":3088.975,"duration":17.79},{"text":"That in approving and authorizing the contract, the officers and board of directors acted in good faith and exercised their independent business judgment that at time of the execution of the contract, Albert Warner, together with the defendants Harry M. Warner and Jack L. Warner, owned less than 20% of the outstanding shares of stock of Warner Brothers Pictures, Inc. and that neither the corporation nor the directors or officers were shown to be at that time or at any time under the domination or control of the three brothers Warner above name that neither the stockholders, its officers or directors were at any time involved in this action antagonistic to the financial interest of the corporation that it is not true either as alleged in the complaint or otherwise that all or a majority or any of the board of directors and officers of Warner Brothers Pictures, Inc. wrongfully participated in the acts in the complaint complained of, nor was said board of directors dominated or controlled by Harry M. Warner, Jack L. Warner and Albert l. Warner, Milton Sperling or anyone or more of them.","start":3088.975,"stop":3165.097,"duration":76.12},{"text":"It is not true that if demand had been made upon Warner Brothers Pictures, Inc. that those to whom such application would be made to institute said act said suit would have been disqualified from faithfully doing their duty as directors and officers of said corporation because of any matters or facts set forth in said complaint or otherwise that no demand was made under directors of Warner Brothers Pictures Incorporated to institute this suit and such demand would have been futile, nor was any demand addressed to the stockholders of said corporation that the stockholders of said corporation --","start":3165.097,"stop":3209.58,"duration":44.48}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"We'll recess now, Mr. Williams.","start":3209.58,"stop":3211.75,"duration":2.17}]},{"speakerName":"Eugene D. Williams","textObjs":[{"text":"All right.","start":3211.75,"stop":3214.95,"duration":3.2}]}]}],"decidedBy":"Warren Court","arguedOn":"Mar  27 - 28, 1957","petitioner":"Smith","respondent":"Sperling","docket":"316","citation":"354 US 91 (1957)","justiaLink":"https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/354/91","lowerCourt":"United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit","grantedOn":"","decidedOn":"Jun 10, 1957"}